INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (60, 21, 'assistant', 'Here are the Business Definitions, Data Classifications, and Data Quality Rules for all fields in the **shipment** sheet.

---

## 📋 Business Definitions

Below are the business definitions for all 30 fields in the shipment dataset.

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A system-generated unique identifier that distinctly identifies each shipment record in the database. Serves as the primary key for the shipment entity and is used to link related records across systems. | Integer / UUID | 100123 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A human-readable alphanumeric reference number assigned to a shipment for business tracking and communication purposes. Used by internal teams, customers, and partners to reference a specific shipment. | VARCHAR(50) | SHP-2024-00456 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Classifies the nature of the shipment in terms of trade direction. Indicates whether goods are being imported into the country or exported out of the country, or in transit. | VARCHAR(20) | IMPORT, EXPORT, TRANSIT |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment was dispatched or handed over to the carrier. Used as the key reference date for trade reporting, customs declarations, and transit time calculations. | DATE (YYYY-MM-DD) | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | The current operational state of the shipment within its lifecycle. Tracks progression from creation through customs clearance to final delivery. Valid values include: Draft, Booked, In Transit, Customs Hold, Delivered, Cancelled. | VARCHAR(30) | In Transit |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the country from which the shipment originates. Used for customs declarations, trade statistics, and regulatory compliance. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | SA, US, CN |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the country where the shipment is ultimately destined. Essential for customs processing, duty calculation, and trade reporting. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | AE, GB, DE |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port, airport, or terminal where the cargo is loaded onto the primary mode of transport. Critical for bill of lading issuance and freight calculation. | VARCHAR(100) | Jeddah Islamic Port / SAJED |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port, airport, or terminal where the cargo is offloaded from the primary carrier. Used in freight documentation and customs entry at destination. | VARCHAR(100) | Dubai Port / AEDXB |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate delivery location of the shipment beyond the port of discharge. May be a city, warehouse, or full address when the port of discharge differs from where goods are finally delivered. | VARCHAR(200) | Riyadh Central Warehouse |
| incoterm_code | Incoterm Code | The International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) trade term code that defines the responsibilities, risks, and costs between the seller and buyer during shipment. Governs who pays freight, insurance, and customs duties. | CHAR(3) | FOB, CIF, EXW, DDP |
| transport_mode | Transport Mode | The primary mode of transportation used to carry the shipment. Determines applicable regulations, documentation requirements, and transit time expectations. Valid values: Sea, Air, Road, Rail, Multimodal. | VARCHAR(20) | Sea |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The legal or trade name of the shipping company, airline, or logistics provider responsible for transporting the shipment. Used for vendor management, freight invoice matching, and claim processing. | VARCHAR(150) | Maersk Line |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel / Flight Number | The identifier of the specific vessel (ship name) or flight number used to transport the shipment. Required for sea and air shipment tracking and customs documentation. | VARCHAR(50) | MSC OSCAR / SV812 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique reference number of the Bill of Lading (B/L), a legal document issued by the carrier to acknowledge receipt of cargo for sea freight. Serves as a document of title and contract of carriage. | VARCHAR(50) | MAEU123456789 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique reference number of the Air Waybill (AWB), a non-negotiable transport document issued by an airline or freight forwarder for air cargo. Serves as a contract of carriage for air shipments. | VARCHAR(20) | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The ISO 6346-compliant unique identifier assigned to a shipping container. Consists of a 4-letter owner code, 6-digit serial number, and 1 check digit. Used for container tracking across ports and terminals. | CHAR(11) | MSCU1234567 |
| container_type | Container Type | The standardized type and size of the shipping container used. Defines the physical dimensions and suitability for cargo type. Common values: 20GP, 40GP, 40HC, 20RF (Reefer), 20OT (Open Top). | VARCHAR(10) | 40HC |
| seal_no | Seal Number | The unique identifier of the tamper-evident security seal affixed to the container door. Used by customs authorities and carriers to verify container integrity during transit. | VARCHAR(30) | SL9874321 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment including all goods, packaging, pallets, and dunnage, measured in kilograms. Used for freight rate calculation, weight declarations, and transport compliance. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 15250.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The weight of the actual goods only, excluding all packaging materials, measured in kilograms. Used for customs valuation, duty calculation, and trade statistics reporting. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 12800.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total volume of the shipment measured in cubic meters (CBM). Used for volumetric freight rate calculation and space planning on vessels or aircraft. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 28.500 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual packages, cartons, pallets, or pieces that make up the shipment. Required for packing list verification, cargo manifests, and customs declarations. | INTEGER | 120 |
| package_type | Package Type | The type of packaging unit used for the shipment goods. Defines how goods are unitized for handling and transport. Examples: Carton, Pallet, Drum, Bag, Crate, Bundle. | VARCHAR(50) | Carton |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code in which the freight charges are denominated and invoiced. Used for financial reporting, foreign exchange conversion, and invoice reconciliation. | CHAR(3) | USD, SAR, EUR |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total freight charges payable to the carrier for transporting the shipment, expressed in the freight currency. Includes base freight rate and applicable surcharges. | DECIMAL(15,2) | 3500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The monetary value of the cargo insurance premium or insured amount associated with the shipment. Expressed in the same or related currency as the freight amount. | DECIMAL(15,2) | 250.00 |
| created_by | Created By | The unique identifier or username of the system user or process that originally created the shipment record. Used for audit trail, accountability, and data lineage tracking. | VARCHAR(100) | john.doe / USR-0042 |
| created_at | Record Creation Timestamp | The system-generated date and timestamp recording when the shipment record was first created in the system. Used for audit logging, data lineage, and SLA monitoring. | TIMESTAMP (UTC) | 2024-03-10 08:45:22 |
| updated_at | Record Last Updated Timestamp | The system-generated date and timestamp recording when the shipment record was most recently modified. Automatically updated on any field change. Used for change tracking and data synchronization. | TIMESTAMP (UTC) | 2024-03-15 14:30:05 |

---

## 🔐 Data Classification

Below is the SDAIA NDMO data classification for all shipment fields.

| Field Name | Classification Level | Classification Rationale | Data Owner | Sensitivity Category |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Restricted | Internal system identifier; no direct business harm if disclosed externally but intended for internal use only. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_ref_no | Restricted | Business reference used internally and shared with partners; limited harm if disclosed beyond authorized parties. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_type | Public | General classification (Import/Export) with no sensitivity; commonly reported in trade statistics. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| shipment_date | Restricted | Operational date with minor commercial sensitivity; could reveal trade patterns if aggregated. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_status | Restricted | Internal operational status; disclosure could expose business operations to unauthorized parties. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| origin_country_code | Restricted | Trade route information with minor commercial sensitivity; aggregated data can reveal supply chain patterns. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| destination_country_code | Restricted | Trade route information with minor commercial sensitivity; aggregated data can reveal distribution strategies. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| port_of_loading | Restricted | Operational logistics detail shared with partners; minor harm if broadly disclosed. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| port_of_discharge | Restricted | Operational logistics detail; minor commercial sensitivity related to supply chain routing. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| final_destination | Confidential | May contain specific facility or client delivery addresses; disclosure could expose client locations or confidential distribution points. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Location Data |
| incoterm_code | Restricted | Commercial trade term; part of contract terms with minor sensitivity. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| transport_mode | Public | General logistics descriptor with no material harm if disclosed. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| carrier_name | Restricted | Commercial vendor relationship data; disclosure of carrier selection could reveal procurement strategies. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| vessel_flight_no | Restricted | Operational transport identifier; limited harm but intended for authorized stakeholders. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| bill_of_lading_no | Confidential | Legal document of title for goods; unauthorized disclosure could enable cargo fraud or theft. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Legal / Financial Data |
| awb_no | Confidential | Legal air transport document; unauthorized use could enable cargo fraud or shipment diversion. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Legal / Financial Data |
| container_no | Confidential | Unique container identifier; unauthorized access could facilitate cargo tampering or theft. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Security Data |
| container_type | Restricted | General cargo specification; minor sensitivity related to cargo planning. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| seal_no | Confidential | Security seal identifier; disclosure could compromise cargo integrity and customs security controls. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Security Data |
| gross_weight_kg | Restricted | Physical shipment metric; minor commercial sensitivity when linked to specific shipments. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| net_weight_kg | Restricted | Cargo weight metric used in duty calculation; minor sensitivity related to customs declarations. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| volume_cbm | Restricted | Cargo volume metric; minor commercial sensitivity when used to infer shipment value or size. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| total_packages | Restricted | Shipment count metric; limited harm if disclosed but intended for internal and partner use. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| package_type | Restricted | Packaging descriptor; minor operational sensitivity. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| freight_currency | Restricted | Financial denomination indicator; limited sensitivity on its own. | Finance / Treasury | Financial Data |
| freight_amount | Confidential | Commercial financial data representing contractual freight costs; disclosure could harm competitive positioning and reveal pricing agreements. | Finance / Treasury | Financial Data |
| insurance_amount | Confidential | Financial data representing insurance coverage; disclosure reveals cargo valuation and financial exposure. | Finance / Treasury | Financial Data |
| created_by | Confidential | Contains user identity information linked to system actions; disclosure could violate employee privacy under Saudi PDPL. | IT / Data Governance | Personal Data (PII) |
| created_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp; limited sensitivity but forms part of the audit trail. | IT / Data Governance | Audit Data |
| updated_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp; limited sensitivity but essential for change tracking and data integrity. | IT / Data Governance | Audit Data |

---

## ✅ Data Quality Rules

Below are the data quality rules for all shipment fields across key DQ dimensions.

| Field Name | DQ Dimension | DQ Rule | DQ Threshold | DQ Priority |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Completeness | Every shipment record must have a non-null shipment_id. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_id | Uniqueness | No two shipment records may share the same shipment_id. | 100% unique — zero duplicates tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_id | Validity | shipment_id must be a positive integer or valid UUID format only. | 100% conformance | Critical |
| shipment_ref_no | Completeness | shipment_ref_no must not be null or empty for any active shipment. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_ref_no | Uniqueness | shipment_ref_no must be unique across all records. | 100% unique | High |
| shipment_ref_no | Validity | Must follow the defined format pattern (e.g., SHP-YYYY-#####). | ≥ 98% conformance | High |
| shipment_type | Completeness | shipment_type must be populated for every shipment record. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_type | Validity | Value must be one of the approved domain values: IMPORT, EXPORT, TRANSIT. | 100% conformance to allowed values | Critical |
| shipment_date | Completeness | shipment_date must not be null for any shipment record. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_date | Validity | Date must be a valid calendar date in YYYY-MM-DD format and not a future date beyond today + 30 days. | 100% valid dates | Critical |
| shipment_date | Accuracy | shipment_date must not precede the company''s founding date or any logical minimum date (e.g., 2000-01-01). | 100% within valid range | High |
| shipment_status | Completeness | shipment_status must not be null for any record. | 100% | Critical |
| shipment_status | Validity | Must be one of the approved statuses: Draft, Booked, In Transit, Customs Hold, Delivered, Cancelled. | 100% conformance | Critical |
| shipment_status | Consistency | If shipment_status = Delivered, then updated_at must be populated and shipment_date must not be null. | 100% | High |
| origin_country_code | Completeness | origin_country_code must not be null. | 100% | Critical |
| origin_country_code | Validity | Must be a valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code from the approved reference list. | 100% conformance | Critical |
| destination_country_code | Completeness | destination_country_code must not be null. | 100% | Critical |
| destination_country_code | Validity | Must be a valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code from the approved reference list. | 100% conformance | Critical |
| destination_country_code | Consistency | destination_country_code must not equal origin_country_code for EXPORT or IMPORT shipment types. | 100% | High |
| port_of_loading | Completeness | port_of_loading must be populated for all sea and air shipments. | ≥ 99% for Sea/Air transport modes | High |
| port_of_loading | Validity | Must be a valid UN/LOCODE or match an approved port reference list. | ≥ 95% conformance | Medium |
| port_of_discharge | Completeness | port_of_discharge must be populated for all sea and air shipments. | ≥ 99% for Sea/Air transport modes | High |
| port_of_discharge | Validity | Must be a valid UN/LOCODE or match an approved port reference list. | ≥ 95% conformance | Medium |
| final_destination | Completeness | final_destination must not be null for shipments with incoterm DDP, DAP, or DAT. | 100% for applicable incoterms | High |
| incoterm_code | Completeness | incoterm_code must not be null for any shipment. | 100% | High |
| incoterm_code | Validity | Must be one of the 11 ICC-approved Incoterm 2020 codes: EXW, FCA, CPT, CIP, DAP, DPU, DDP, FAS, FOB, CFR, CIF. | 100% conformance | High |
| transport_mode | Completeness | transport_mode must not be null for any shipment record. | 100% | Critical |
| transport_mode | Validity | Must be one of: Sea, Air, Road, Rail, Multimodal. | 100% conformance | Critical |
| transport_mode | Consistency | If transport_mode = Sea, then bill_of_lading_no must be populated. If transport_mode = Air, then awb_no must be populated. | 100% | High |
| carrier_name | Completeness | carrier_name must not be null for any booked or in-transit shipment. | ≥ 99% for active shipments | High |
| carrier_name | Accuracy | carrier_name must match an approved carrier master list to avoid free-text entry errors. | ≥ 95% match rate | Medium |
| vessel_flight_no | Completeness | vessel_flight_no must be populated for Sea and Air shipments. | ≥ 98% for Sea/Air modes | High |
| vessel_flight_no | Validity | For air shipments, must follow IATA flight number format (e.g., XX999). | ≥ 95% conformance | Medium |
| bill_of_lading_no | Completeness | bill_of_lading_no must be populated for all sea freight shipments. | 100% for Sea transport mode | Critical |
| bill_of_lading_no | Uniqueness | bill_of_lading_no must be unique across all sea shipment records. | 100% unique | High |
| awb_no | Completeness | awb_no must be populated for all air freight shipments. | 100% for Air transport mode | Critical |
| awb_no | Uniqueness | awb_no must be unique across all air shipment records. | 100% unique | High |
| awb_no | Validity | Must conform to IATA AWB format: 3-digit airline code + hyphen + 8-digit number (e.g., 176-12345678). | ≥ 98% conformance | High |
| container_no | Completeness | container_no must be populated for all FCL (Full Container Load) sea shipments. | ≥ 99% for FCL shipments | High |
| container_no | Validity | Must conform to ISO 6346 format: 4 letters + 6 digits + 1 check digit (e.g., MSCU1234567). | 100% conformance | High |
| container_type | Completeness | container_type must not be null when container_no is present. | 100% when container_no exists | High |
| container_type | Validity | Must be one of approved ISO container type codes: 20GP, 40GP, 40HC, 20RF, 40RF, 20OT, 45HC. | 100% conformance | Medium |
| seal_no | Completeness | seal_no must be populated for all containerized shipments. | ≥ 99% for containerized cargo | High |
| gross_weight_kg | Completeness | gross_weight_kg must not be null for any shipment. | 100% | Critical |
| gross_weight_kg | Validity | Must be a positive numeric value greater than zero. | 100% positive values | Critical |
| gross_weight_kg | Accuracy | gross_weight_kg must be greater than or equal to net_weight_kg at all times. | 100% — gross ≥ net | Critical |
| net_weight_kg | Completeness | net_weight_kg must not be null for any shipment. | 100% | Critical |
| net_weight_kg | Validity | Must be a positive numeric value greater than zero and ≤ gross_weight_kg. | 100% | Critical |
| volume_cbm | Completeness | volume_cbm must not be null for sea freight shipments. | ≥ 99% for Sea mode | High |
