INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (64, 23, 'assistant', 'Here are the business definitions for all 30 fields in the **shipment** table:

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A system-generated unique numeric or alphanumeric identifier assigned to each shipment record at the time of creation. Serves as the primary key for the shipment entity and is used to reference the shipment across all related systems and tables. | Integer / UUID | 100123 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A human-readable business reference number assigned to the shipment, often generated by the shipper or logistics team. Used for tracking, communication, and cross-referencing with external parties such as freight forwarders and customs brokers. | VARCHAR | SHP-2024-00456 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Indicates the direction and nature of the shipment movement. Typically distinguishes between import (goods arriving into the country) and export (goods leaving the country), and may also include transit or re-export categories. | VARCHAR (Lookup) | Import, Export, Transit |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment is dispatched from the origin location or port of loading. Used as the primary business date for reporting, compliance, and timeline tracking. | DATE | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Represents the current lifecycle stage of the shipment within the logistics and customs workflow. Tracks progression from creation through to final delivery or closure. | VARCHAR (Lookup) | Draft, In Transit, Cleared, Delivered, Cancelled |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the country from which the goods originate or are exported. Used for trade statistics, customs declarations, and regulatory compliance. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | SA, US, CN |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the country to which the goods are being shipped or imported. Used for trade reporting, tariff determination, and sanctions screening. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | AE, GB, DE |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port, airport, or terminal where the goods are physically loaded onto the carrier (vessel, aircraft, or truck). A key field in the Bill of Lading and customs documentation. | VARCHAR | Jeddah Islamic Port, SAJED |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port, airport, or terminal where the goods are unloaded from the primary carrier. May differ from the final destination if onward transport is required. | VARCHAR | Dubai Port, AEDXB |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate delivery location of the goods, which may be a city, address, warehouse, or facility. Differs from port of discharge when inland transport or transshipment is involved. | VARCHAR | Riyadh Logistics Hub, Warehouse B |
| incoterm_code | Incoterm Code | The internationally recognized trade term (as defined by the International Chamber of Commerce) that specifies the responsibilities of buyers and sellers regarding delivery, risk transfer, and cost allocation. | CHAR(3) (Lookup) | FOB, CIF, EXW, DDP |
| transport_mode | Transport Mode | The primary mode of transportation used to move the goods from origin to destination. Determines the applicable documentation, regulations, and carrier type. | VARCHAR (Lookup) | Sea, Air, Road, Rail, Multimodal |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The legal or commercial name of the transportation company (shipping line, airline, trucking company, or rail operator) responsible for physically transporting the goods. | VARCHAR | Saudi Airlines Cargo, MSC Shipping |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel / Flight Number | The identifier of the specific vessel (ship name or IMO number) or flight number used to transport the goods. Used for tracking, customs declarations, and ETA monitoring. Applicable to sea and air shipments respectively. | VARCHAR | MSC ANNA / SV 1234 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique reference number of the Bill of Lading (B/L), which is the legal contract between the shipper and the ocean carrier. Acts as a title document for the goods and is required for customs clearance of sea shipments. | VARCHAR | MSCUSA1234567 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique reference number of the Air Waybill (AWB), which is the contract of carriage for air freight shipments. Required for customs clearance and cargo tracking of air shipments. Follows IATA format (3-digit airline code + 8-digit serial number). | VARCHAR | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The unique ISO 6346-compliant identifier assigned to the shipping container used to transport the goods. Consists of a 4-letter owner code, 6-digit serial number, and 1 check digit. Used for tracking and customs examination. | CHAR(11) | MSCU1234567 |
| container_type | Container Type | Specifies the ISO standard type and size of the shipping container used. Determines capacity, applicable freight rates, and handling requirements at ports. | VARCHAR (Lookup) | 20GP, 40GP, 40HC, 20RF, 40OT |
| seal_no | Seal Number | The unique identifier of the security seal applied to the container or cargo unit after loading. Used by customs authorities to verify that the container has not been tampered with during transit. | VARCHAR | SL-9987654 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment including goods, packaging, and any other materials, measured in kilograms. Used for freight calculation, carrier capacity planning, and customs declarations. Must be greater than zero. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 12500.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The weight of the goods alone, excluding packaging and container materials, measured in kilograms. Used for customs valuation, duty calculation, and trade statistics. Must be less than or equal to gross weight. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 11800.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total volume of the shipment measured in cubic meters (CBM). Used for freight rate calculation (volumetric weight), container utilization, and capacity planning. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 45.750 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual packages, cartons, pallets, or units that make up the shipment. Used in customs declarations, cargo manifests, and receiving verification. | INTEGER | 240 |
| package_type | Package Type | Describes the type of packaging used for the shipment goods. Used for handling instructions, storage requirements, and customs documentation. | VARCHAR (Lookup) | Carton, Pallet, Drum, Crate, Bag |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code in which the freight charges are quoted and invoiced. Used for financial reporting, foreign exchange conversion, and cost accounting. | CHAR(3) | SAR, USD, EUR |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total cost of transporting the goods from origin to destination as agreed with the carrier, expressed in the freight currency. Includes base freight rate and applicable surcharges. Excludes insurance. | DECIMAL(15,2) | 18500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The value of the cargo insurance premium or insured amount associated with the shipment, expressed in the freight currency. Used for risk management, financial reporting, and claims processing. | DECIMAL(15,2) | 2500.00 |
| created_by | Created By | The username, employee ID, or system identifier of the user or automated process that initially created the shipment record in the system. Used for audit trail and accountability purposes. | VARCHAR | ahmed.ali / SYSTEM |
| created_at | Created At | The system-recorded timestamp indicating the exact date and time when the shipment record was first created in the system. Used for audit logging, data lineage, and SLA tracking. Stored in UTC. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-10 08:45:00 |
| updated_at | Updated At | The system-recorded timestamp indicating the most recent date and time when the shipment record was modified. Automatically updated on every record change. Used for change tracking, data freshness monitoring, and audit purposes. Stored in UTC. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15 14:22:00 |', '2026-03-04 03:35:17.29777');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (65, 23, 'user', 'ok give me data classification for all fields ', '2026-03-04 03:35:58.448155');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (66, 23, 'assistant', 'Here are the SDAIA NDMO data classifications for all fields in the **shipment** table:

| Field Name | Classification Level | Classification Rationale | Data Owner | Sensitivity Category |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Restricted | Internal system identifier with no direct public value; exposure could enable unauthorized tracking or system enumeration. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Internal Identifier |
| shipment_ref_no | Restricted | Business reference used internally and shared with authorized trading partners; limited exposure risk but not intended for public disclosure. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Internal Identifier |
| shipment_type | Public | General categorical indicator (Import/Export/Transit) that carries no sensitive information on its own. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_date | Restricted | Transaction date that when combined with other fields could reveal business activity patterns, trade volumes, or operational schedules. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_status | Restricted | Internal workflow status; disclosure could reveal operational vulnerabilities or enable interference with active shipments. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| origin_country_code | Restricted | Country-level trade origin data; aggregated disclosure could reveal sourcing strategies and supply chain dependencies. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| destination_country_code | Restricted | Country-level trade destination data; aggregated disclosure could reveal market strategies and distribution networks. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| port_of_loading | Restricted | Specific port information linked to shipment routing; could expose logistical strategies and supply chain structure if disclosed broadly. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| port_of_discharge | Restricted | Specific port information linked to shipment routing; could expose logistical strategies and supply chain structure if disclosed broadly. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| final_destination | Confidential | Contains specific delivery locations such as warehouse addresses and facility names; disclosure could compromise security of goods and business confidentiality. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Location & Operational Data |
| incoterm_code | Restricted | Reveals contractual trade terms between buyer and seller; disclosure could expose negotiated commercial arrangements. | Trade Finance / Legal | Commercial Data |
| transport_mode | Public | General category of transportation mode with no sensitive business information on its own. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| carrier_name | Restricted | Identifies specific carrier relationships and preferred logistics partners; disclosure could reveal vendor selection and procurement strategy. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| vessel_flight_no | Restricted | Vessel or flight identifiers linked to active shipments; disclosure in real time could raise security or cargo interference concerns. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| bill_of_lading_no | Confidential | A legally binding title document number; unauthorized disclosure could enable cargo fraud, document forgery, or unauthorized cargo release. | Logistics / Trade Finance | Legal & Financial Document |
| awb_no | Confidential | Air Waybill number is a legal transport contract reference; unauthorized disclosure could enable cargo fraud or unauthorized tracking and interception. | Logistics / Trade Finance | Legal & Financial Document |
| container_no | Confidential | Unique container identifier; disclosure of active container numbers could pose a physical security risk and enable cargo theft or tampering. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Security-Sensitive Data |
| container_type | Restricted | Container specifications that reveal cargo handling requirements; limited sensitivity but restricted to authorized parties. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| seal_no | Confidential | Security seal identifiers are used by customs to verify cargo integrity; disclosure could enable seal forgery or tampering and compromise customs security. | Customs / Logistics Operations | Security-Sensitive Data |
| gross_weight_kg | Restricted | Weight data linked to specific shipments; aggregated disclosure could reveal trade volumes and cargo capacity utilization. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| net_weight_kg | Restricted | Cargo weight excluding packaging; used in duty calculations and trade statistics; restricted to authorized internal and customs use. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| volume_cbm | Restricted | Volumetric data used for freight costing; limited sensitivity individually but contributes to commercial intelligence when aggregated. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| total_packages | Restricted | Package count linked to specific shipments; contributes to cargo manifest data restricted to authorized parties. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| package_type | Restricted | Packaging type reveals cargo handling needs and may indicate the nature of goods; restricted to authorized operational users. | Logistics / Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| freight_currency | Confidential | Currency denomination of freight transactions reveals financial arrangements and foreign exchange exposure of the business. | Trade Finance / Finance | Financial Data |
| freight_amount | Confidential | Actual freight cost is commercially sensitive financial data; disclosure could expose negotiated carrier rates and cost structures, violating commercial confidentiality. | Trade Finance / Finance | Financial Data |
| insurance_amount | Confidential | Insurance values reflect the declared value of goods and financial risk exposure; disclosure could violate commercial confidentiality and financial privacy obligations. | Trade Finance / Finance | Financial Data |
| created_by | Confidential | Contains user identifiers or employee IDs linked to individuals; constitutes personal data subject to privacy protection under PDPL and NDMO guidelines. | Data Governance / IT | Personal Data (PII) |
| created_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp; restricted to internal audit and governance use; not sensitive individually but part of the audit trail. | Data Governance / IT | Audit & Metadata |
| updated_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp recording last modification; restricted to internal audit and governance use as part of the data change trail. | Data Governance / IT | Audit & Metadata |', '2026-03-04 03:36:25.374545');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (67, 23, 'user', 'ok give me data quality rules for each field ', '2026-03-04 03:37:09.812148');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (68, 23, 'assistant', 'Here are the data quality rules for all fields in the **shipment** table:

| Field Name | DQ Dimension | DQ Rule | DQ Threshold | DQ Priority |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Completeness | Every shipment record must have a non-null, non-empty shipment_id. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_id | Uniqueness | Each shipment_id must be unique across the entire shipment table; no duplicate primary keys permitted. | 100% — zero duplicates tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_id | Validity | shipment_id must conform to the defined format (numeric integer or UUID pattern) and must not contain special characters or spaces. | 100% — zero format violations tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_ref_no | Completeness | Every shipment record must have a non-null shipment_ref_no assigned before the record is approved or submitted. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_ref_no | Uniqueness | Each shipment_ref_no must be unique across all shipment records to prevent duplicate business references. | 100% — zero duplicates tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_ref_no | Validity | shipment_ref_no must follow the defined business naming convention (e.g., SHP-YYYY-NNNNN) and must not exceed the maximum defined character length. | 98% conformance or above | High |
| shipment_type | Completeness | shipment_type must not be null for any shipment record; every shipment must be classified by type. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_type | Validity | shipment_type must only contain values from the approved reference list (e.g., Import, Export, Transit, Re-Export). No free-text or unlisted values permitted. | 100% — zero invalid values tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_date | Completeness | shipment_date must not be null for any shipment record. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_date | Validity | shipment_date must be a valid calendar date in the format YYYY-MM-DD and must not be a future date beyond the allowable planning horizon (e.g., not more than 30 days in the future). | 100% — zero invalid dates tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_date | Consistency | shipment_date must not be later than the created_at timestamp and must be logically consistent with port_of_loading activity dates. | 99% consistency or above | High |
| shipment_status | Completeness | shipment_status must not be null for any record; all shipments must have a defined status at all times. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_status | Validity | shipment_status must only contain values from the approved status reference list (e.g., Draft, In Transit, Cleared, Delivered, Cancelled). | 100% — zero invalid values tolerated | Critical |
| shipment_status | Consistency | shipment_status transitions must follow the defined business workflow sequence (e.g., Draft → In Transit → Cleared → Delivered); backward or invalid transitions must be flagged. | 100% — zero invalid transitions tolerated | High |
| origin_country_code | Completeness | origin_country_code must not be null for any shipment record. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| origin_country_code | Validity | origin_country_code must be a valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 code from the approved country reference table. | 100% — zero invalid codes tolerated | Critical |
| origin_country_code | Consistency | origin_country_code must not be identical to destination_country_code for standard import/export shipments; same-country records must be flagged for review. | 100% — zero same-origin-destination pairs tolerated | High |
| destination_country_code | Completeness | destination_country_code must not be null for any shipment record. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| destination_country_code | Validity | destination_country_code must be a valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 code from the approved country reference table. | 100% — zero invalid codes tolerated | Critical |
| destination_country_code | Consistency | destination_country_code must align with the final_destination field; the country of the final destination address must match the destination_country_code. | 98% consistency or above | High |
| port_of_loading | Completeness | port_of_loading must not be null for sea and air shipments; may be conditionally optional for road/rail transport modes. | 100% for sea/air shipments | Critical |
| port_of_loading | Validity | port_of_loading must match a valid entry in the approved UN/LOCODE port reference table. | 98% conformance or above | High |
| port_of_loading | Consistency | port_of_loading must be located in or associated with the origin_country_code country. | 99% consistency or above | High |
| port_of_discharge | Completeness | port_of_discharge must not be null for sea and air shipments. | 100% for sea/air shipments | Critical |
| port_of_discharge | Validity | port_of_discharge must match a valid entry in the approved UN/LOCODE port reference table. | 98% conformance or above | High |
| port_of_discharge | Consistency | port_of_discharge must be located in or associated with the destination_country_code country. | 99% consistency or above | High |
| final_destination | Completeness | final_destination must not be null; every shipment must have a defined ultimate delivery location. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| final_destination | Validity | final_destination must not exceed the maximum character limit and must not contain invalid characters or placeholder values such as "TBD" or "N/A" on finalized shipments. | 98% conformance or above | High |
| incoterm_code | Completeness | incoterm_code must not be null for any shipment record; trade terms must be defined for every shipment. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| incoterm_code | Validity | incoterm_code must only contain values from the official ICC Incoterms reference list (e.g., EXW, FOB, CIF, DDP, DAP, CPT). | 100% — zero invalid values tolerated | Critical |
| incoterm_code | Consistency | incoterm_code must be consistent with the transport_mode (e.g., FOB and CIF are only valid for sea transport; FCA is applicable to all modes). | 98% consistency or above | High |
| transport_mode | Completeness | transport_mode must not be null for any shipment record. | 100% — zero nulls tolerated | Critical |
| transport_mode | Validity | transport_mode must only contain values from the approved reference list (e.g., Sea, Air, Road, Rail, Multimodal). | 100% — zero invalid values tolerated | Critical |
| transport_mode | Consistency | transport_mode must be consistent with the presence of related fields: sea shipments must have bill_of_lading_no and container_no; air shipments must have awb_no. | 99% consistency or above | High |
| carrier_name | Completeness | carrier_name must not be null for any finalized or in-transit shipment record. | 100% for non-draft shipments | High |
| carrier_name | Validity | carrier_name must match an entry in the approved carrier master reference table; free-text entries not in the reference list must be flagged for review. | 95% conformance or above | Medium |
| carrier_name | Accuracy | carrier_name must be verified against the carrier master data to ensure correct spelling and legal entity name; abbreviated or informal names must be standardized. | 95% accuracy or above | Medium |
| vessel_flight_no | Completeness | vessel_flight_no must not be null for sea and air shipments; conditionally optional for road and rail transport modes. | 100% for sea/air shipments | High |
| vessel_flight_no | Validity | vessel_flight_no must follow the expected format: IATA flight number format for air (e.g., SV1234) or vessel name/IMO number format for sea shipments. | 98% conformance or above | High |
| bill_of_lading_no | Completeness | bill_of_lading_no must not be null for all sea freight shipments; must be null or empty for air and road shipments unless explicitly applicable. | 100% for sea shipments | Critical |
| bill_of_lading_no | Uniqueness | Each bill_of_lading_no must be unique within the shipment table to prevent duplicate documentation. | 100% — zero duplicates tolerated | Critical |
| bill_of_lading_no | Validity | bill_of_lading_no must conform to the carrier-specific B/L numbering format and must not contain spaces or special characters. | 98% conformance or above | High |
| awb_no | Completeness | awb_no must not be null for all air freight shipments; must be null or empty for sea and road shipments unless explicitly applicable. | 100% for air shipments | Critical |
| awb_no | Uniqueness | Each awb_no must be unique within the shipment table to prevent duplicate air waybill references. | 100% — zero duplicates tolerated | Critical |
| awb_no | Validity | awb_no must follow the IATA standard format: 3-digit airline prefix followed by an 8-digit serial number (e.g., 176-12345678). | 98% conformance or above | High |
| container_no | Completeness | container_no must not be null for FCL (Full Container Load) sea shipments; conditionally optional for LCL and non-sea shipments. | 100% for FCL sea shipments | Critical |
| container_no | Uniqueness | Each container_no must be unique per shipment leg; duplicate container numbers on the same shipment must be flagged. | 100% — zero duplicates per shipment | High |
| container_no | Validity | container_no must conform to ISO 6346 format: 4 uppercase letters (owner code) + 6 digits (serial number) + 1 check digit (e.g., MSCU1234567). | 100% — zero format violations tolerated | Critical |
| container_type | Completeness | container_type must not be null when container_no is populated; both fields must be present together. | 100% when container_no is present | High |
| container_type | Validity | container_type must only contain values from the ISO standard container type reference list (e.g., 20GP, 40GP, 40HC, 20RF, 40OT). | 100% — zero invalid values tolerated | High |
