Saudi Arabia
This factsheet provides the latest statistics on trade and investment between the UK and Saudi Arabia.
Date of release: 2 February 2026; Date of next planned release: 26 March 2026
Total trade in goods and services (exports plus imports) between the UK and Saudi Arabia1 was £16.6 billion in the four
quarters to the end of Q3 2025, an increase of 2.9% or £468 million in current prices from the four quarters to the end of Q3
2024. Of this £16.6 billion:
• Total UK exports to Saudi Arabia amounted to £13.2 billion in the four quarters to the end of Q3 2025 (an increase of
4.9% or £615 million in current prices, compared to the four quarters to the end of Q3 2024);
• Total UK imports from Saudi Arabia amounted to £3.5 billion in the four quarters to the end of Q3 2025 (a decrease of
4.1% or £147 million in current prices, compared to the four quarters to the end of Q3 2024).
Saudi Arabia was the UK’s 24th largest trading partner in the four quarters to the end of Q3 2025 accounting for 0.9% of
total UK trade.2
At the end of 2024, the stock of FDI from the UK in Saudi Arabia was £6.5 billion, 3.4% or £211 million higher than the
end of 2023. At the end of 2024, Saudi Arabia accounted for 0.4% of the total UK outward FDI stock.
At the end of 2024, the stock of FDI from Saudi Arabia in the UK are not available due to data disclosure.3
1‘the four quarters to the end of Q3 2025’ refers to the 12 months to the end of September 2025
2Trade data sourced from the latest ONS publication of UK total trade: all countries seasonally adjusted data.
3Investment data sourced from the ONS ad-hoc data release if not provided in the latest ONS main FDI release.
