INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (95, 36, 'assistant', 'Here are the key insights from the UK–Saudi Arabia Trade and Investment Factsheet (released February 2026):

---

## 🇸🇦🇬🇧 UK–Saudi Arabia Trade & Investment: Key Insights

---

### 1. 📊 Overall Trade Relationship

| Metric | Value | Trend |
|---|---|---|
| Total bilateral trade (Q3 2025 rolling) | £16.6 billion | ▲ +2.9% (+£468M) |
| Total bilateral trade (2024 calendar year) | £16.2 billion | ▼ -4.1% (-£700M) |
| Saudi Arabia''s rank as UK trading partner | **24th** | Stable |

> **Insight**: On a rolling 12-month basis the relationship is growing, but the 2024 full-year figure declined — suggesting the recovery is a **recent trend driven by 2025 momentum**.

---

### 2. 📤 UK Exports to Saudi Arabia (Strong Growth)

| Category | Rolling Q3 2025 | 2024 Full Year |
|---|---|---|
| **Total exports** | £13.2B ▲ +4.9% | £13.0B ▲ +4.0% |
| Goods | £4.9B (37%) ▲ +3.4% | £4.7B (36%) ▼ -9.1% |
| **Services** | **£8.3B (63%)** ▲ +5.8% | **£8.3B (64%)** ▲ +13.3% |
| Export rank | **21st** | **19th** |

> **Key Insight**: The UK export relationship is **services-dominated** (63%+). Services exports grew an impressive **+13.3% in 2024**, making this the primary growth engine. This aligns with Saudi Vision 2030''s demand for professional, financial, and consulting services.

---

### 3. 📥 UK Imports from Saudi Arabia (Declining)

| Category | Rolling Q3 2025 | 2024 Full Year |
|---|---|---|
| **Total imports** | £3.5B ▼ -4.1% | £3.3B ▼ **-26.8%** |
| Goods | £2.2B (63%) ▼ -9.4% | £2.1B (63%) ▼ **-35.4%** |
| Services | £1.3B (37%) ▲ +6.3% | £1.2B (37%) ▼ -5.1% |
| Import rank | **37th** | **38th** |

> **Key Insight**: UK imports from Saudi Arabia dropped sharply — goods imports fell **35.4% in 2024**, likely driven by **lower oil/energy prices** and reduced commodity flows. This creates a very **asymmetric trade balance strongly in the UK''s favor** (£13B exports vs £3.3B imports).

---

### 4. 💹 Trade Balance Summary

| Period | UK Exports | UK Imports | UK Trade Surplus |
|---|---|---|---|
| Rolling Q3 2025 | £13.2B | £3.5B | **+£9.7B** |
| 2024 Calendar Year | £13.0B | £3.3B | **+£9.7B** |

> **Insight**: The UK runs a **massive trade surplus** of nearly £10 billion with Saudi Arabia — one of its largest bilateral surpluses globally. Saudi Arabia is far more important as an **export destination** than an import source for the UK.

---

### 5. 🌍 UK Market Share in Saudi Arabia

| Segment | 2024 Market Share | Change vs 2023 |
|---|---|---|
| Total trade | 5.2% | ▼ -0.1 pp |
| Goods only | 2.8% | ▼ -0.6 pp |
| **Services only** | **10.4%** | ▲ **+1.1 pp** |

> **Key Insight**: The UK holds a **dominant 10.4% share** of Saudi Arabia''s services imports — a strategically strong position. However, goods market share is slipping, suggesting competitive pressure from other exporters in manufactured/commodity goods.

---

### 6. 💰 Foreign Direct Investment (FDI)

| FDI Direction | Value (End 2024) | Change vs 2023 |
|---|---|---|
| UK → Saudi Arabia (Outward) | **£6.5 billion** | ▲ +3.4% (+£211M) |
| Saudi Arabia → UK (Inward) | **Not available** | Data withheld (disclosure rules) |

> **Key Insight**: UK investment in Saudi Arabia is growing steadily and stands at £6.5B, representing **0.4% of total UK outward FDI** globally. The absence of inward FDI data (Saudi → UK) is a transparency gap — in reality, Saudi sovereign wealth (PIF) investments in UK assets are significant but not captured here.

---

### 7. 🔑 Strategic Takeaways

| # | Insight |
|---|---|
| 1 | **Services are the backbone** of UK–Saudi trade and growing fast — driven by Vision 2030 demand for expertise |
| 2 | **Goods trade is weakening** on both sides — UK goods exports dipped in 2024; Saudi goods imports (energy) fell sharply |
| 3 | **Massive trade surplus** (~£9.7B) in UK''s favor — Saudi Arabia is a net buyer of UK value |
| 4 | **UK market share in Saudi services (10.4%)** is high and rising — a competitive advantage to protect |
| 5 | **FDI data gap** on Saudi inward investment into UK limits full picture of the financial relationship |
| 6 | Data quality note: **2019–2022 figures were volatile** due to COVID, supply chains, and Brexit — caution needed for trend analysis spanning that period |

---

*Data sourced from ONS, HMRC, OECD, and UNCTAD. Factsheet released by UK Department for Business and Trade, 2 February 2026.*', '2026-03-04 08:52:19.802627');
