## 1. Business Definitions

Here are the business definitions for all 30 fields in the shipment imports dataset.

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A unique system-generated identifier assigned to each shipment record at the time of creation. Serves as the primary key for the shipment entity and is used to reference the shipment across all related systems and documents. | VARCHAR(20) | SHP-000001 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A business-facing reference number assigned to the shipment, typically generated by the logistics or trade system. Used by stakeholders (importers, exporters, brokers) to track and communicate about a specific shipment. May differ from the internal shipment_id. | VARCHAR(30) | REF-115659-SX |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Categorizes the direction of the shipment relative to Saudi Arabia. Valid values include "Import" (goods entering KSA) and "Export" (goods leaving KSA). Determines applicable customs procedures, duties, and regulatory requirements under ZATCA jurisdiction. | VARCHAR(20) | Import |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment was initiated, dispatched, or recorded as active. Stored as a numeric serial date (Excel format) and should be converted to a standard DATE format (YYYY-MM-DD). Used for duty calculation, timeline tracking, and compliance reporting. | DATE | 2023-08-14 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Indicates the current operational status of the shipment within its lifecycle. Valid values include: Pending, At Port, In Transit, Cleared, Delivered, Cancelled. Drives workflow actions, alerts, and reporting dashboards. | VARCHAR(30) | At Port |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code representing the country from which the shipment originated. Used to determine trade agreements, tariff rates, rules of origin, and import duty applicability. | CHAR(2) | CN |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code representing the country to which the shipment is destined. Used alongside origin country code to determine applicable trade routes, export controls, and bilateral agreements. | CHAR(2) | SA |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name of the port or terminal where the cargo was loaded onto the primary mode of transport. Used for routing, bill of lading issuance, and freight cost calculation. Relevant for sea and rail shipments. | VARCHAR(100) | Ningbo Port |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name of the port or terminal where the cargo is offloaded from the primary carrier. For Saudi imports, this is typically a Saudi seaport or land border crossing under ZATCA oversight. | VARCHAR(100) | King Abdulaziz Port Dammam |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate delivery location or facility where the goods are to be received after customs clearance. May differ from the port of discharge when goods are transported inland after arrival. | VARCHAR(150) | King Abdulaziz Port Dammam |
| incoterm_code | Incoterms Code | The International Commercial Terms (Incoterms) code agreed upon between the buyer and seller, defining the responsibilities for transportation costs, insurance, and risk transfer. Valid values per ICC Incoterms 2020: EXW, FCA, FAS, FOB, CFR, CIF, CPT, CIP, DAP, DPU, DAT, DDP. | CHAR(3) | FCA |
| transport_mode | Transport Mode | The primary mode of transportation used for the shipment. Valid values include: Sea, Air, Road, Rail, Multimodal. Determines applicable documentation (Bill of Lading vs AWB), carrier types, and transit time expectations. | VARCHAR(20) | Sea |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The name of the shipping line, airline, or logistics company responsible for transporting the goods. Used for carrier performance tracking, freight cost analysis, and dispute resolution. | VARCHAR(100) | CMA CGM |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel or Flight Number | The identifier of the specific vessel (for sea/rail) or flight (for air transport) carrying the shipment. Format varies by transport mode: vessel voyage numbers (e.g., V-HQH168) or flight codes. Used for tracking and port arrival notifications. | VARCHAR(30) | V-HQH168 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique reference number of the Bill of Lading (B/L), a legal document issued by the carrier acknowledging receipt of cargo for shipment. Serves as a contract of carriage, title document, and receipt. Applicable for sea shipments. Must be unique per shipment. | VARCHAR(30) | BL6724959017 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique reference number of the Air Waybill (AWB), a non-negotiable transport document used for air freight shipments. Applicable only when transport_mode = ''Air''. Expected to be blank for sea/road/rail shipments. | VARCHAR(20) | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The internationally standardized unique identifier of the shipping container, following ISO 6346 format (4 letters + 7 digits, e.g., ILGN8753883). Used for container tracking, terminal operations, and customs examination. | VARCHAR(15) | ILGN8753883 |
| container_type | Container Type | The standardized type code of the shipping container used. Common values include: 20GP (20-foot General Purpose), 40GP (40-foot General Purpose), 40HC (40-foot High Cube), 20OT (20-foot Open Top), 20RF (Reefer). Determines cargo capacity and handling requirements. | VARCHAR(10) | 40HC |
| seal_no | Seal Number | The unique identifier of the security seal applied to the container after loading and before departure. Used by customs authorities, including ZATCA, to verify container integrity and detect tampering during transit. | VARCHAR(20) | SL128015 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment including goods, packaging, and container tare weight, measured in kilograms. Used for freight cost calculation, customs declaration, and transport compliance. Must be greater than zero and greater than or equal to net weight. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 160.67 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The weight of the goods only, excluding packaging and container, measured in kilograms. Used for duty calculation, cargo manifests, and trade statistics. Must be less than or equal to gross weight and greater than zero. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 143.74 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total volume of the shipment measured in cubic meters (CBM - Cubic Meters). Used for freight rate calculation (volumetric weight), container utilization analysis, and space planning. Must be greater than zero. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 0.28 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual packages, units, or pieces included in the shipment. Used for cargo manifests, customs declarations, and warehouse receiving. Must be a positive integer greater than zero. | INTEGER | 90 |
| package_type | Package Type | The type of packaging used for the goods in the shipment. Common values include: Carton, Drum, Bale, Crate, Pallet, Loose, Box, Bag. Used for handling instructions, stowage planning, and customs inspection. | VARCHAR(30) | Drum |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code in which the freight amount is denominated. Valid values include: USD, SAR, EUR, AED, GBP, etc. Must be consistent with the freight_amount field for financial reporting and VAT calculation. | CHAR(3) | USD |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total cost charged for transporting the shipment from origin to destination, expressed in the currency specified in freight_currency. Used for customs valuation (CIF/FOB basis), VAT calculation, and freight cost analysis. Must be a non-negative number. | DECIMAL(15,2) | 55.17 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The cost of cargo insurance associated with the shipment, expressed in the same currency as freight_currency. Used in customs valuation calculations (CIF = Cost + Insurance + Freight). Must be a non-negative number. | DECIMAL(15,2) | 1.38 |
| created_by | Created By | The username or system identifier of the user or process that created the shipment record in the system. Used for audit trail, accountability tracking, and data lineage purposes. Should reference a valid user account in the identity management system. | VARCHAR(50) | user_023 |
| created_at | Created At | The timestamp at which the shipment record was first created in the system, stored as a numeric serial date-time (Excel format). Should be converted to TIMESTAMP format (YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS). Used for audit trails and SLA monitoring. | TIMESTAMP | 2023-08-13 00:00:00 |
| updated_at | Last Updated At | The timestamp of the most recent modification made to the shipment record, stored as a numeric serial date-time (Excel format). Should be converted to TIMESTAMP format. Used for change tracking, data freshness monitoring, and audit compliance. | TIMESTAMP | 2023-08-20 13:00:00 |

