INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (113, 42, 'assistant', 'Here are the business definitions for the 30 fields in the **shipment** table:

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A system-generated unique identifier that distinctly identifies each shipment record in the database. Serves as the primary key of the shipment entity and is used to link related records across all downstream tables. Must be unique, non-null, and immutable once assigned. | INTEGER / BIGINT | 100001 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A business-facing alphanumeric reference number assigned to a shipment, used for communication with carriers, freight forwarders, customs authorities, and trading partners. Unlike the internal shipment_id, this reference may follow a human-readable naming convention (e.g., prefix + year + sequence). Must be unique per shipment. | VARCHAR(50) | SHP-2024-00123 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Classifies the shipment as an import, export, re-export, or transit movement. Drives regulatory treatment, customs declaration requirements, and applicable ZATCA customs procedures. Valid values are typically: IMPORT, EXPORT, RE-EXPORT, TRANSIT. | VARCHAR(20) | EXPORT |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment departed from the origin point or was handed over to the carrier. Used as the primary business date for customs declarations, duty calculations, and reporting periods. Format: YYYY-MM-DD. | DATE | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Represents the current lifecycle stage of the shipment within the logistics and customs clearance workflow. Valid values may include: DRAFT, SUBMITTED, IN_TRANSIT, CUSTOMS_HOLD, CLEARED, DELIVERED, CANCELLED. Drives downstream processing and notifications. | VARCHAR(30) | IN_TRANSIT |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the country from which the shipment originated. Used in customs declarations, trade statistics, rules-of-origin determinations, and applicable trade agreements. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | SA |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the final country to which the shipment is being sent. Used in customs processing, export controls, sanctions screening, and trade statistics reporting. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | AE |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name or UN/LOCODE of the seaport, airport, or land border crossing where the shipment was loaded onto the primary means of transport. Required for customs declarations and Bill of Lading / Air Waybill documentation. | VARCHAR(100) | SAJED (Jeddah Islamic Port) |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name or UN/LOCODE of the seaport, airport, or land border crossing where the shipment is scheduled to be unloaded from the primary means of transport. Required for arrival declarations and customs clearance at destination. | VARCHAR(100) | AEDXB (Dubai Port) |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate delivery address or location where the goods are to be received by the consignee. May differ from the port of discharge when inland transportation is involved. Used for last-mile logistics planning and customs documentation. | VARCHAR(255) | Dubai Logistics City, UAE |
| incoterm_code | Incoterm Code | The International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) Incoterms® trade term code that defines the responsibilities of the buyer and seller regarding delivery, risk transfer, and cost allocation. Valid values are the 11 standard Incoterms 2020 codes (e.g., EXW, FOB, CIF, DDP, DAP, FCA, CPT, CIP, DAT, CFR, FAS). Directly impacts customs valuation and insurance requirements. | CHAR(3) | FOB |
| transport_mode | Transport Mode | The primary mode of transportation used for the shipment. Valid values typically include: SEA, AIR, LAND, RAIL, MULTIMODAL. Determines which transport document applies (Bill of Lading for sea, Air Waybill for air) and applicable customs procedures. | VARCHAR(20) | SEA |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The full legal or trade name of the shipping company, airline, or freight carrier responsible for transporting the goods. Used in customs declarations, freight invoicing, and carrier performance tracking. | VARCHAR(200) | Maersk Line |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel or Flight Number | The identifier of the vessel (ship name or IMO number) or flight number used to transport the shipment. For sea freight, this is the vessel name or voyage number; for air freight, it is the IATA flight number. Used in arrival/departure manifests and customs pre-arrival notifications. | VARCHAR(50) | MSC ANNA / EK-802 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique alphanumeric number assigned to the Bill of Lading (B/L), which is the official contract of carriage between the shipper and the sea carrier. The B/L is a title document and is required for customs clearance of sea freight shipments. Applicable only when transport_mode = SEA. | VARCHAR(50) | MAEU1234567890 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique number assigned to the Air Waybill (AWB), which is the contract of carriage for air freight shipments. Follows the IATA format: 3-digit airline prefix + 8-digit serial number (e.g., 176-12345678). Applicable only when transport_mode = AIR. Used for customs clearance and cargo tracking. | VARCHAR(20) | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The unique alphanumeric identifier assigned to a shipping container, following the ISO 6346 standard format: 4 letters (owner code + equipment category) + 6 digits + 1 check digit (e.g., MSCU1234567). Applicable for containerized sea freight. Used for cargo tracking, port operations, and customs documentation. | VARCHAR(15) | MSCU1234567 |
| container_type | Container Type | The standardized type and size classification of the shipping container used. Common values include: 20GP (20-foot General Purpose), 40GP (40-foot General Purpose), 40HC (40-foot High Cube), 20RF (20-foot Refrigerated), 40RF (40-foot Refrigerated), OT (Open Top), FR (Flat Rack). Affects freight rate calculation and stowage planning. | VARCHAR(10) | 40HC |
| seal_no | Container Seal Number | The unique identifier of the tamper-evident seal applied to the container or cargo unit at the point of loading. Used by customs authorities to verify that the container has not been opened or tampered with during transit. Required for customs documentation and security compliance (e.g., C-TPAT, AEO). | VARCHAR(50) | SL-9876543 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (kg) | The total weight of the shipment including all goods, packaging materials, pallets, and the container tare weight, expressed in kilograms. Used for freight rate calculation, weight-based duty assessment, and transport capacity planning. Must be a positive numeric value. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 24500.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (kg) | The weight of the actual goods only, excluding all packaging materials, pallets, and containers, expressed in kilograms. Used for customs duty calculation, statistical reporting, and regulatory compliance. Must be a positive numeric value and must not exceed gross_weight_kg. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 22000.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total volume of the shipment expressed in cubic meters (CBM — Cubic Meter). Used for freight rate calculation under volumetric/dimensional weight pricing, container utilization analysis, and warehouse planning. Must be a positive numeric value. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 45.250 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual packages, cartons, pallets, or other packing units comprising the shipment. Used in customs declarations, packing lists, and carrier documentation. Must be a positive integer. | INTEGER | 150 |
| package_type | Package Type | The type of packaging used for the shipment goods. Common values include: CARTON, PALLET, CRATE, DRUM, BAG, ROLL, BUNDLE, BOX, LOOSE. Used in packing list documentation and customs declarations. | VARCHAR(50) | CARTON |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code representing the currency in which the freight charges are denominated (e.g., SAR, USD, EUR, AED). Must be a valid ISO 4217 code and must align with the currency of freight_amount. Used in financial reporting and customs valuation. | CHAR(3) | USD |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total freight charges paid or payable for transporting the shipment, expressed in the currency specified by freight_currency. Used in customs valuation (CIF value calculation), financial reporting, and cost analysis. Must be a non-negative numeric value with two decimal places. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 3500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The total cost of cargo insurance premium paid for the shipment, expressed in the currency specified by freight_currency. Required for CIF (Cost, Insurance, Freight) customs valuation calculations. Must be a non-negative numeric value. A value of 0.00 is acceptable if no insurance was obtained. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 175.00 |
| created_by | Created By | The unique identifier or username of the system user or integration account that originally created the shipment record. Used for audit trail, data lineage, and accountability tracking. Should reference a valid user record in the user/identity management system. | VARCHAR(100) | usr_ahmed.ali |
| created_at | Record Creation Timestamp | The system-generated date and time at which the shipment record was first created in the system, stored in UTC. Used for audit logging, data lineage, and record lifecycle management. Must be automatically populated by the system and must never be modified after initial creation. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-10 08:30:00 |
| updated_at | Record Last Updated Timestamp | The system-generated date and time at which the shipment record was most recently modified, stored in UTC. Automatically updated by the system on every record modification. Used for change tracking, data synchronization, and audit purposes. Must always be greater than or equal to created_at. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15 14:22:10 |', '2026-03-04 13:12:56.501133');
