INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (115, 43, 'assistant', 'Here are the business definitions for all fields in the **shipment** sheet:

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A unique system-generated identifier assigned to each shipment record in ZATCA''s import/export tracking system. Serves as the primary key for the shipment entity and is used to reference the shipment across all related tables and processes. | INTEGER / BIGINT | 100001 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A human-readable business reference number assigned to the shipment, typically generated by the customs authority or the declarant''s system. Used for cross-referencing with customs declarations, manifests, and trader communications. | VARCHAR(50) | SHP-2024-00123 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Classifies the nature and direction of the shipment. Indicates whether the shipment involves goods entering (import), leaving (export), transiting (transit), or being temporarily admitted into Saudi Arabia. Drives applicable customs procedures and regulatory requirements. | VARCHAR(20) | IMPORT, EXPORT, TRANSIT, RE-EXPORT |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment was dispatched from the origin point or presented to customs authorities. Used as the reference date for customs duty calculations, tariff applicability, and VAT determination under ZATCA regulations. | DATE | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Represents the current lifecycle stage of the shipment within the customs and logistics workflow. Tracks the shipment from initial registration through customs clearance to final delivery. Valid values reflect the customs process stages defined by ZATCA. | VARCHAR(30) | PENDING, CLEARED, HELD, REJECTED, IN_TRANSIT, DELIVERED |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 standardized country code representing the country from which the goods originated or were shipped. Used for country-of-origin declarations, preferential tariff determination, and trade statistics reporting. | CHAR(2) / CHAR(3) | SA, AE, CN, US |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 standardized country code representing the country to which the goods are ultimately consigned. Used for export control compliance, trade flow analytics, and customs routing decisions. | CHAR(2) / CHAR(3) | SA, GB, DE, JP |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name or UN/LOCODE identifier of the seaport, airport, or land border crossing where the goods were loaded onto the primary means of transport. Critical for determining freight routes, transit declarations, and bill of lading verification. | VARCHAR(100) | Jeddah Islamic Port, Dubai Port (AEDXB) |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name or UN/LOCODE identifier of the seaport, airport, or land border crossing where the goods are unloaded from the primary means of transport. Used to validate the customs entry point and align with the customs declaration. | VARCHAR(100) | King Abdulaziz Port Dammam, Rotterdam Port |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate delivery address, city, or location where the goods are to be delivered to the consignee after customs clearance. May differ from the port of discharge when inland transportation is involved. Used for risk profiling and logistics coordination. | VARCHAR(255) | Riyadh, King Khalid Industrial City |
| incoterm_code | Incoterm Code | The standardized International Commercial Terms (Incoterms) code as published by the International Chamber of Commerce (ICC), defining the responsibilities, costs, and risk transfer point between the buyer and seller. Determines the taxable base for customs valuation under ZATCA''s rules. | CHAR(3) | EXW, FOB, CIF, DAP, DDP |
| transport_mode | Transport Mode | Identifies the primary mode of transport used to carry the shipment. Determines applicable customs procedures, documentation requirements (e.g., bill of lading vs. AWB), and freight cost treatment for customs valuation purposes. | VARCHAR(20) | SEA, AIR, LAND, RAIL, MULTIMODAL |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The legal name of the shipping company, airline, or freight operator responsible for transporting the goods. Used for manifest matching, carrier licensing verification, and liability determination during transit. | VARCHAR(150) | Saudi Airlines Cargo, Maersk Line, DHL Express |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel or Flight Number | The unique identifier assigned to the specific voyage (for sea freight) or flight (for air freight) carrying the shipment. Used to match cargo manifests, track arrival/departure schedules, and validate customs entry documentation. | VARCHAR(50) | MSC ANNA V.001, SV-724, CMA-CGM-0089 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique number assigned to the Bill of Lading (B/L) — the legal document issued by the carrier acknowledging receipt of cargo for sea shipments. Serves as a contract of carriage and document of title. Mandatory for sea freight customs clearance under ZATCA. | VARCHAR(100) | MAEU123456789, CMDU987654321 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique identifier assigned to the Air Waybill (AWB) — the non-negotiable transport document issued for air freight shipments. Equivalent to the bill of lading for air cargo. Required for air shipment customs clearance. Follows the IATA AWB numbering format (3-digit airline code + 8-digit serial number). | VARCHAR(20) | 176-12345678, 020-98765432 |
| container_no | Container Number | The unique ISO 6346-compliant alphanumeric identifier assigned to the shipping container. Follows the format: 4-letter owner code + 6-digit serial number + check digit (e.g., MSCU1234567). Used for container tracking, port operations, and customs physical inspection targeting. | VARCHAR(20) | MSCU1234567, TCKU3456789 |
| container_type | Container Type | Classifies the standardized type and size of the shipping container used, based on ISO standards. Determines cargo capacity, handling procedures, and applicable freight rates. Common types include standard dry, refrigerated (reefer), open top, flat rack, and tank containers. | VARCHAR(30) | 20GP, 40HC, 40RF, 20OT, FLATRACK |
| seal_no | Container Seal Number | The unique identifier of the tamper-evident seal affixed to the container at the time of loading. Verified by customs inspectors upon arrival to confirm the container has not been opened or tampered with during transit. A broken or mismatched seal triggers mandatory physical inspection. | VARCHAR(50) | SL-9874563, CUSTOMS-00123 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment including all goods, packaging materials, pallets, and container tare weight, expressed in kilograms. Used for freight cost calculation, customs duty assessment on weight-based tariffs, and transport compliance with road/air weight limits. | DECIMAL(15,3) | 12500.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The weight of the goods themselves excluding all packaging, pallets, and dunnage, expressed in kilograms. The net weight is the primary basis for customs duty calculation under specific tariff codes and is declared on the customs entry and commercial invoice. | DECIMAL(15,3) | 11200.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (Cubic Meters) | The total volumetric measurement of the shipment expressed in cubic meters (CBM). Used for ocean freight rate calculation (when volumetric weight exceeds actual weight), warehouse space planning, and container utilization assessment. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 28.500 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual handling units (boxes, cartons, pallets, drums, etc.) comprising the shipment. Declared on the packing list and customs entry. Used for customs physical examination, cargo reconciliation, and manifest verification. | INTEGER | 250 |
| package_type | Package Type | Describes the type of packaging used for the individual handling units within the shipment. Based on UN/CEFACT package type codes or standard industry terms. Relevant for customs documentation, cargo handling instructions, and dangerous goods classification. | VARCHAR(50) | CARTON, PALLET, DRUM, CRATE, BAG, ROLL |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code in which the freight charges are denominated and invoiced by the carrier. Required for customs valuation (CIF value calculation) and financial reporting. Must be converted to SAR for ZATCA customs duty and VAT assessment. | CHAR(3) | USD, EUR, SAR, GBP |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total freight charges payable to the carrier for transporting the goods, expressed in the freight currency. A mandatory component of the CIF (Cost, Insurance, Freight) customs valuation formula used by ZATCA to determine the assessable value for customs duty and import VAT. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 3500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The total insurance premium paid or payable to insure the goods during transit, expressed in the freight currency. Combined with freight charges and goods cost (FOB value) to compute the CIF value for customs duty and VAT assessment under ZATCA''s customs valuation rules. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 175.50 |
| created_by | Created By | The unique identifier or username of the system user or automated process that created the shipment record. Used for data lineage tracking, audit trail maintenance, and accountability in ZATCA''s data governance framework. | VARCHAR(100) | usr_ahmed.ali, system_api, admin |
| created_at | Record Creation Timestamp | The system-generated timestamp recording the exact date and time when the shipment record was first created in the system. Used for audit trails, SLA tracking, data lineage, and chronological sequencing of events. Must be stored in UTC or Saudi Arabia Standard Time (AST, UTC+3). | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15 08:30:00 |
| updated_at | Record Last Update Timestamp | The system-generated timestamp recording the date and time of the most recent modification made to the shipment record. Automatically updated on every record change. Used for change tracking, data synchronization, incremental data loads, and audit compliance. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15 14:45:00 |', '2026-03-04 13:14:10.994805');
