INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (129, 48, 'assistant', 'Here are the business definitions for the fields in the **shipment** sheet:

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A system-generated unique identifier assigned to each shipment record in the system. This is the primary key used internally to reference and link shipment records across all related tables. It must be unique, non-null, and immutable once assigned. | INTEGER / BIGINT | 100001 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A human-readable, business-assigned reference number used to identify and track a shipment across internal departments and with external parties (carriers, customs, brokers). May follow a structured naming convention (e.g., SHP-2024-00123). Must be unique per shipment. | VARCHAR(50) | SHP-2024-00123 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Indicates the direction and nature of the shipment in terms of trade flow. Common values are IMPORT (goods arriving into Saudi Arabia), EXPORT (goods leaving Saudi Arabia), and TRANSIT (goods passing through). Drives applicable customs procedures and regulatory requirements. | VARCHAR(20) | IMPORT, EXPORT, TRANSIT |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment was dispatched from the origin point or the date recorded on the transport document (e.g., Bill of Lading date or Airway Bill date). Used as the key reference date for customs declarations, duty calculations, and SLA tracking. Format: YYYY-MM-DD. | DATE | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Represents the current lifecycle stage of the shipment within the logistics and customs clearance process. Defines the state machine progression of a shipment. Valid values may include: DRAFT, BOOKED, IN_TRANSIT, AT_PORT, UNDER_INSPECTION, CLEARED, DELIVERED, CANCELLED. | VARCHAR(30) | IN_TRANSIT |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 standard code representing the country from which the shipment originates (country of export). Used in customs declarations, trade statistics reporting, and rules-of-origin determination. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | SA, CN, US, DE |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 standard code representing the country to which the shipment is ultimately destined (country of import). Used in customs clearance, trade agreement applicability, and export control checks. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | SA, AE, GB, JP |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port, airport, or terminal where the cargo is physically loaded onto the main transport vehicle or vessel for international carriage. Corresponds to the "Port of Loading" field on the Bill of Lading or Airway Bill. | VARCHAR(100) | Jeddah Islamic Port, Shanghai Port |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port, airport, or terminal where the cargo is unloaded from the main international carrier. This is the first point of arrival in the destination country and the location where customs clearance typically initiates. | VARCHAR(100) | King Abdulaziz Port - Dammam |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate physical delivery address, city, or location where the cargo is to be delivered after customs clearance and last-mile logistics. This may differ from the port of discharge when inland transportation is involved. | VARCHAR(255) | Riyadh Industrial City, Warehouse 7 |
| incoterm_code | Incoterm Code | The standardized International Commercial Terms (Incoterms) code published by the International Chamber of Commerce (ICC) that defines the responsibilities, costs, and risks between the buyer and seller in the shipment. Valid values follow the Incoterms 2020 standard: EXW, FCA, CPT, CIP, DAP, DPU, DDP, FAS, FOB, CFR, CIF. Critical for determining customs value and freight cost treatment. | CHAR(3) | FOB, CIF, DAP, EXW |
| transport_mode | Mode of Transport | The primary mode of transportation used to carry the shipment internationally. Determines applicable transport documents, customs procedures, and regulatory requirements. Valid values: SEA, AIR, ROAD, RAIL, MULTIMODAL. Aligns with customs declaration transport mode codes. | VARCHAR(20) | SEA, AIR, ROAD, RAIL |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The full legal or commercial name of the transportation company (shipping line, airline, trucking company, or rail operator) responsible for physically transporting the shipment. Used for carrier performance tracking and document verification. | VARCHAR(200) | Saudi Airlines Cargo, COSCO Shipping |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel / Flight Number | The vessel name (for sea freight) or flight number (for air freight) or truck/train identifier (for road/rail) on which the shipment is loaded. Used to track the physical movement of cargo and link to transport schedules and manifests. | VARCHAR(50) | MSC SARA, SV-1234 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique reference number of the Bill of Lading (B/L), which is the legally binding document issued by the carrier acknowledging receipt of cargo for sea shipments. It serves as the title document for the goods and is mandatory for sea freight customs clearance. Applicable when transport_mode = SEA. | VARCHAR(50) | COSU1234567890 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique reference number of the Air Waybill (AWB), the transport contract and receipt issued by an airline or freight forwarder for air cargo shipments. It is non-negotiable and serves as the key document for air freight customs clearance. Applicable when transport_mode = AIR. Format typically follows IATA standard: XXX-XXXXXXXX. | VARCHAR(20) | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The internationally standardized ISO 6346 identifier of the shipping container used to carry the cargo. Format: 4 letters (owner code + equipment category) + 6 digits + 1 check digit (e.g., MSCU1234567). Applicable for containerized sea or rail shipments. Used for port terminal tracking and customs inspection. | VARCHAR(15) | MSCU1234567 |
| container_type | Container Type | The ISO standard type and size classification of the shipping container. Defines the physical dimensions and special features of the container. Common values: 20GP (20-foot General Purpose), 40GP (40-foot General Purpose), 40HC (40-foot High Cube), 20RF (Refrigerated), 40OT (Open Top). | VARCHAR(10) | 20GP, 40HC, 40RF |
| seal_no | Container Seal Number | The unique identifier of the tamper-evident security seal affixed to the container door at the point of stuffing. Used by customs authorities to verify container integrity and detect unauthorized access during transit. Must be recorded and verified upon arrival at the port of discharge. | VARCHAR(50) | SEAL-2024-98765 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment including all goods, packaging materials, pallets, and the container/unit load device (ULD) where applicable, measured in kilograms. Used for freight charge calculations, vessel/aircraft load planning, and customs declaration. Must be a positive numeric value. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 15250.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The weight of the actual goods only, excluding all packaging materials, pallets, and containers, measured in kilograms. Used for customs duty assessment (when duties are specific/per kg), trade statistics, and commercial invoice verification. Must be less than or equal to gross_weight_kg. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 12800.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total volumetric measurement of the shipment expressed in cubic meters (CBM = Length × Width × Height in meters). Used for freight rate calculations (volumetric weight vs. actual weight), container capacity planning, and warehousing. Must be a positive value. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 48.500 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual handling units (boxes, cartons, pallets, drums, bags, etc.) that make up the shipment. Must be a positive integer. Used in packing list verification, customs examination, and cargo receipt confirmation. | INTEGER | 250 |
| package_type | Package Type | The type or form of the individual handling unit used to pack the goods. Defines how goods are physically consolidated for transport. Common values: CARTON, PALLET, DRUM, BAG, CRATE, BUNDLE, ROLL, CYLINDER. Aligns with customs declaration package type codes. | VARCHAR(50) | CARTON, PALLET, DRUM |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code of the currency in which the freight charges are invoiced and paid. Used for financial reporting, customs value determination, and foreign currency conversion. Must be a valid ISO 4217 code. | CHAR(3) | SAR, USD, EUR |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total freight charges payable for the transportation of the shipment, expressed in the currency specified in freight_currency. This value is a critical component of the customs value calculation (CIF basis) and must be accurately declared. Must be a non-negative numeric value with up to 2 decimal places. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 12500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The total cost of cargo insurance premium paid to insure the shipment during transit, expressed in the same currency as freight_currency. Required for CIF (Cost, Insurance, Freight) Incoterm valuation and for customs duty base calculation. Must be a non-negative numeric value. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 875.50 |
| created_by | Created By | The system username, user ID, or employee identifier of the person or system process that originally created the shipment record in the system. Used for audit trail, accountability, and data lineage tracking. Should reference a valid user in the user management system. | VARCHAR(100) | usr_admin01, SYSTEM |
| created_at | Record Creation Timestamp | The system-generated date and time at which the shipment record was first created in the database, recorded in UTC or local Saudi Arabia time (AST, UTC+3). Immutable after record creation. Used for audit logging, SLA measurement, and data lineage. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-10 08:45:22 |
| updated_at | Record Last Updated Timestamp | The system-generated date and time at which the shipment record was most recently modified, recorded in UTC or local Saudi Arabia time (AST, UTC+3). Automatically updated by the system on every record modification. Must always be greater than or equal to created_at. Used for change tracking and data freshness monitoring. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15 14:22:10 |', '2026-03-04 13:59:52.652833');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (130, 48, 'user', 'do data classifcation ', '2026-03-04 14:01:07.364077');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (131, 48, 'assistant', 'Here are the data classification assignments for the fields in the **shipment** sheet, aligned with the Saudi SDAIA NDMO data classification framework:

| Field Name | Classification Level | Classification Rationale | Data Owner | Sensitivity Category |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Restricted | Internal system identifier with no standalone sensitivity, but links to sensitive shipment records. Disclosure could enable unauthorized record access or enumeration attacks. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Internal Reference Data |
| shipment_ref_no | Restricted | Business reference number used internally and shared with trusted trade partners. Disclosure to unauthorized parties could enable tracking or manipulation of trade transactions. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Internal Reference Data |
| shipment_type | Public | General classification of trade direction (IMPORT/EXPORT/TRANSIT). No harm from disclosure; commonly referenced in trade statistics and public customs data. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| shipment_date | Restricted | Transaction date tied to a specific commercial shipment. When combined with other fields, could reveal trade patterns or be used to challenge customs declarations. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| shipment_status | Restricted | Operational status of a shipment within customs and logistics processes. Unauthorized disclosure could expose clearance stage and enable circumvention of inspection procedures. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| origin_country_code | Public | ISO standard country code representing the country of origin. Widely used in trade documents and publicly declared in customs manifests. No harm from standalone disclosure. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| destination_country_code | Public | ISO standard country code for the shipment destination. Publicly declared in shipping documents and trade statistics. No standalone sensitivity. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| port_of_loading | Public | Name of the departure port or airport. Appears on publicly available shipping manifests, Bills of Lading, and carrier schedules. No sensitivity in isolation. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Logistics & Transport Data |
| port_of_discharge | Public | Name of the arrival port or airport. Publicly referenced in shipping documents, vessel schedules, and port manifests. No standalone sensitivity. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Logistics & Transport Data |
| final_destination | Confidential | Ultimate physical delivery address of goods. May contain specific warehouse addresses, facility names, or business locations of importers/exporters. Disclosure could compromise business security or enable theft of high-value cargo. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Commercial & Business Data |
| incoterm_code | Restricted | Defines the contractual obligations between buyer and seller regarding cost and risk transfer. Disclosure could reveal negotiated trade terms and commercial arrangements between parties. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Commercial & Business Data |
| transport_mode | Public | General mode of transport (SEA/AIR/ROAD/RAIL). Commonly declared in customs documents and trade statistics. No harm from disclosure in isolation. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Logistics & Transport Data |
| carrier_name | Restricted | Name of the transportation company handling the shipment. When combined with other fields, could reveal preferred carrier relationships, trade routes, and contracted logistics arrangements. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Commercial & Business Data |
| vessel_flight_no | Restricted | Specific vessel or flight identifier carrying the cargo. Could be used to track cargo movements and combined with other data to identify shipment contents or schedules. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Logistics & Transport Data |
| bill_of_lading_no | Confidential | Legally binding transport document number that serves as the title of goods for sea freight. Unauthorized access could enable cargo fraud, document forgery, or unlawful release of goods. Subject to customs authority confidentiality requirements. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Legal & Regulatory Document Data |
| awb_no | Confidential | Air Waybill number serving as the air freight transport contract reference. Unauthorized disclosure could enable cargo tracking exploitation, document fraud, or goods diversion. Subject to IATA and customs confidentiality requirements. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Legal & Regulatory Document Data |
| container_no | Confidential | Unique container identifier that enables precise cargo tracking and location. Disclosure to unauthorized parties could facilitate cargo theft, tampering, or smuggling intelligence. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Logistics & Transport Data |
| container_type | Restricted | Physical specification of the container used. In combination with cargo details, could reveal storage conditions (e.g., refrigerated = pharmaceutical/food) and enable targeted interception. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Logistics & Transport Data |
| seal_no | Confidential | Security seal number used to verify container integrity. Unauthorized disclosure could enable seal duplication, tampering, or bypassing of customs physical inspection controls. Highly sensitive from a border security perspective. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Security & Compliance Data |
| gross_weight_kg | Restricted | Total shipment weight declared for customs and freight purposes. Combined with cargo type could indicate value or nature of goods. Discrepancies with declared weight trigger customs inspections. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| net_weight_kg | Restricted | Net cargo weight excluding packaging. Directly used in customs duty calculations. Disclosure in combination with other fields could reveal commercial quantities and pricing structures. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| volume_cbm | Restricted | Volumetric measurement of the shipment. Used in freight calculations and container planning. Combined with weight data could reveal cargo density and nature of goods. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| total_packages | Restricted | Count of individual handling units. Used in customs examination and cargo receipt. Discrepancy between declared and actual count is a key customs risk indicator. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| package_type | Restricted | Type of packaging used for the cargo. In combination with cargo description, could indicate handling requirements and nature of goods (e.g., drums may indicate chemicals). | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Trade Operations Data |
| freight_currency | Restricted | Currency of freight payment. Part of customs value calculation. Reveals the currency regime and financial arrangements of the trading entity. | Financial Data Owner | Financial & Commercial Data |
| freight_amount | Confidential | Monetary value of freight charges forming part of the customs dutiable value (CIF basis). Disclosure reveals negotiated freight rates, trade volumes, and commercial relationships. Subject to financial confidentiality and customs valuation regulations. | Financial Data Owner | Financial & Commercial Data |
| insurance_amount | Confidential | Monetary value of cargo insurance premium contributing to customs value calculation. Reveals financial exposure, cargo value estimation, and insurer relationships. Subject to financial confidentiality requirements. | Financial Data Owner | Financial & Commercial Data |
| created_by | Confidential | Username or employee ID of the person who created the shipment record. Constitutes personally identifiable information (PII) linked to an employee or system user. Subject to Saudi PDPL personal data protection requirements. | HR & Identity Data Owner | Personal Data (PII) |
| created_at | Restricted | System timestamp of record creation. Supports audit trail and data lineage. Disclosure of audit timestamps could assist in reconstructing system activity patterns or identifying processing windows. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Audit & Metadata |
| updated_at | Restricted | System timestamp of the most recent record modification. Part of the audit trail. Disclosure could reveal system update patterns and operational processing schedules. | Customs & Trade Data Owner | Audit & Metadata |', '2026-03-04 14:01:42.967577');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (132, 48, 'user', 'I want to scan my data for PII and sensitive information. Please help me understand what you can detect and how the privacy scan works.', '2026-03-04 14:03:59.091716');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (133, 48, 'assistant', 'Great question! Here''s how the **PII & Sensitive Data Privacy Scan** works:

---

## 🔍 What I Can Detect

I analyze every column in your uploaded file across **6 detection categories**:

| Category | Examples |
|---|---|
| **Direct Identifiers** | Full name, National ID, Passport number, Email, Phone number, Employee ID |
| **Quasi Identifiers** | Date of birth, Gender, Nationality, ZIP code, Job title (combinable to identify individuals) |
| **Financial Data** | Bank account numbers, IBAN, Credit card numbers, Salary, Tax amounts |
| **Health Data** | Medical record numbers, Diagnoses, Medications, Insurance policy numbers |
| **Behavioral Data** | Login history, Transaction patterns, Device IDs, IP addresses |
| **Location Data** | GPS coordinates, Home address, Physical delivery address |

---

## ⚖️ Regulatory Framework Applied

- **Saudi PDPL** (Personal Data Protection Law) — determines if data is subject to consent, retention, and processing obligations
- **SDAIA NDMO Classification Standards** — assigns sensitivity classification to each column
- **General PII best practices** — aligned with GDPR, ISO 29101, and DAMA privacy standards

---

## 📋 What the Scan Report Includes

For **every column** in your file, I will return:

- ✅ Whether it is **PII** (true/false)
- ✅ Whether it is **Sensitive** (true/false)
- ✅ **PII Category** (Direct Identifier, Quasi Identifier, Financial, Health, etc.)
- ✅ **PDPL Relevance** (Subject to PDPL / Conditionally Subject / Not Subject)
- ✅ **Risk Level** (Critical / High / Medium / Low)
- ✅ **Recommended Control** (Mask / Encrypt / Tokenize / Anonymize / Restrict Access / No Action)
- ✅ **Actionable Recommendation** per column

---

## 📁 How to Use It

Simply upload your Excel file (with actual data rows) and type one of the following:

> *"Scan this file for PII"*
> *"Run a privacy scan"*
> *"Check this data for sensitive information"*
> *"PDPL compliance check"*

I will analyze the **column names**, **inferred data types**, and **sample data values** to produce a structured JSON privacy report — without ever repeating or exposing your raw data in the response.

---

## ⚠️ Important Notes

- The scan works best when your file contains **actual data rows** (not just headers), as sample values significantly improve detection accuracy
- I analyze a **maximum of 5 sample rows** per column — no full data is stored or reproduced
- Results are based on **column semantics + sample data patterns** — always validate with your Data Privacy Officer before making compliance decisions

---

Ready when you are — just upload your file and trigger the scan! 🚀', '2026-03-04 14:04:15.081712');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (134, 48, 'user', 'give me the PII ', '2026-03-04 14:04:50.754093');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (135, 48, 'assistant', 'It looks like you''d like to run a PII scan, but I need an **uploaded file with actual data** to perform the analysis.

---

## 📂 What I Need From You

Please upload an Excel file that contains:

| Requirement | Details |
|---|---|
| **Column Headers** | The field/column names in the first row |
| **Actual Data Rows** | At least 1–5 rows of real or representative sample data |
| **File Format** | `.xlsx` or `.xls` preferred |

---

## ⚠️ Why I Can''t Scan Yet

The file previously uploaded (**import_export_data_fields.xlsx**) had **no data rows** — all 5 sample rows were empty. Without actual data values, I can only infer PII based on column names alone, which may lead to:

- ❌ **False positives** — flagging non-PII columns incorrectly
- ❌ **False negatives** — missing PII hidden in unexpectedly named columns
- ❌ **Inaccurate risk levels** — unable to confirm sensitivity from values

---

## 💡 What You Can Do

**Option 1 — Upload a new file with data rows:**
> Re-upload the file with at least 5 rows of actual or anonymized sample data

**Option 2 — Request a name-based scan only:**
> Type: *"Run a PII scan based on column names only"* and I will perform a best-effort scan using field name semantics from the **shipment** sheet we already analyzed

---

Which option would you like to proceed with? 🚀', '2026-03-04 14:05:00.346179');
