INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (141, 49, 'assistant', 'Here are the business definitions for the fields in the **shipment** table:

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A system-generated unique identifier that distinctly identifies each shipment record in the system. It serves as the primary key for the shipment entity and is used to reference the shipment across all related tables and processes. | INTEGER / BIGINT | 100123 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A human-readable, business-assigned reference number used to identify and track a shipment across internal and external stakeholders (e.g., freight forwarders, customs authorities, carriers). This number is typically shared with trading partners and may appear on shipping documents. | VARCHAR(50) | SHP-2024-00456 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Categorizes the shipment as either an import, export, re-export, or transit movement. This classification determines the applicable customs procedures, duties, and regulatory requirements under Saudi Customs Authority rules. | VARCHAR(20) | IMPORT, EXPORT, RE-EXPORT, TRANSIT |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment was dispatched from the origin point or handed over to the carrier. This date is used for customs declaration, duty calculation, and trade statistics reporting. | DATE | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Represents the current lifecycle stage of the shipment within the logistics and customs clearance process. Valid statuses typically include: DRAFT, SUBMITTED, IN-TRANSIT, ARRIVED, CLEARED, DELIVERED, CANCELLED. | VARCHAR(30) | IN-TRANSIT |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 standard country code representing the country from which the shipment originated. Used for country-of-origin determination, trade agreement eligibility, and customs declaration. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | SA, US, CN |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 standard country code representing the country to which the shipment is being sent. Used for import customs processing, tariff classification, and trade statistics. | CHAR(2) or CHAR(3) | SA, AE, DE |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name or UN/LOCODE of the seaport, airport, or land border crossing point where the shipment was loaded onto the primary means of transport. This information is mandatory on the Bill of Lading or Airway Bill. | VARCHAR(100) | Jeddah Islamic Port, SAJED |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name or UN/LOCODE of the seaport, airport, or land border crossing point where the shipment is unloaded from the primary means of transport. This is a key field for customs clearance initiation. | VARCHAR(100) | King Abdulaziz Port, SADAM |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate delivery address or location where the shipment''s goods are to be delivered after passing through customs clearance. This may differ from the port of discharge when inland transportation is involved. | VARCHAR(255) | Riyadh Central Warehouse, Al-Kharj Road |
| incoterm_code | Incoterm Code | The internationally recognized trade term (as defined by the International Chamber of Commerce — ICC Incoterms® 2020) that governs the responsibilities, costs, and risk transfer between the seller and the buyer. Valid values include: EXW, FCA, FOB, CFR, CIF, DAP, DDP, etc. | CHAR(3) | FOB, CIF, DAP |
| transport_mode | Transport Mode | Specifies the primary mode of transportation used to carry the shipment from origin to destination. Valid values typically include: SEA, AIR, LAND, RAIL, MULTIMODAL. This field drives the applicable transport documents and customs procedures. | VARCHAR(20) | SEA, AIR, LAND |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The registered name of the shipping company, airline, or logistics provider responsible for physically transporting the shipment. This party is identified on the Bill of Lading (for sea freight) or Airway Bill (for air freight). | VARCHAR(150) | Saudi Airlines Cargo, Maersk Line |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel or Flight Number | The unique identifier assigned by the carrier to the specific vessel voyage or flight that is transporting the shipment. For sea freight, this is the vessel name and voyage number; for air freight, it is the flight number. Used for arrival tracking and customs pre-arrival processing. | VARCHAR(50) | MSC DIANA V.202W, SV-812 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique reference number of the Bill of Lading (B/L), which is the legal document issued by the sea carrier to the shipper acknowledging receipt of the cargo and serving as a contract of carriage and a document of title. Mandatory for sea freight customs clearance. | VARCHAR(50) | MAEU123456789 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique reference number of the Air Waybill (AWB), which is the non-negotiable transport document issued by an airline or freight forwarder for air cargo shipments. It serves as a contract of carriage and a receipt for goods. Follows IATA 11-digit format (e.g., 123-12345678). | VARCHAR(20) | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The internationally standardized identifier assigned to a specific shipping container, following the ISO 6346 standard format (4 letters + 7 digits, e.g., MSCU1234567). Used for container tracking, customs examination, and yard management. | VARCHAR(15) | MSCU1234567 |
| container_type | Container Type | Specifies the ISO standard type and size of the shipping container used for the shipment. Common values include: 20GP (20-foot General Purpose), 40GP (40-foot General Purpose), 40HC (40-foot High Cube), RF (Reefer), OT (Open Top), FR (Flat Rack). | VARCHAR(10) | 20GP, 40HC, RF |
| seal_no | Seal Number | The unique identifier of the security seal affixed to the shipping container or cargo unit after loading. The seal number is recorded for customs security compliance and is verified at the port of discharge to detect any tampering during transit. | VARCHAR(50) | SL-9987654 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment in kilograms, including the weight of the goods, all packaging materials, and pallets, but excluding the container tare weight. This figure is declared on the shipping documents and is used for freight cost calculation and customs declaration. Must be a positive numeric value. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 15250.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The actual weight of the goods in kilograms, excluding all packaging materials, pallets, and containers. The net weight is used for customs duty calculation, trade statistics, and compliance with weight-based tariff lines. Must be less than or equal to gross_weight_kg. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 14800.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total volume of the shipment measured in cubic meters (CBM — Cubic Meter). This figure is used to calculate volumetric weight for freight pricing (especially for air and LCL sea freight) and for container space planning. Must be a positive numeric value. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 32.750 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual packages, cartons, crates, or handling units that make up the shipment. This figure is declared on the packing list and Bill of Lading/AWB and is verified during customs examination. Must be a positive integer. | INTEGER | 240 |
| package_type | Package Type | Describes the type of packaging used for the shipment''s goods. Common values include: CARTON, PALLET, CRATE, DRUM, BAG, ROLL, BUNDLE. This information appears on the packing list and is used during customs physical examination. | VARCHAR(30) | CARTON, PALLET, DRUM |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code representing the currency in which the freight charges are invoiced and paid. This is required for customs valuation purposes under the GATT Customs Valuation Agreement as applied by Saudi Customs. | CHAR(3) | SAR, USD, EUR |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total freight charges payable to the carrier for transporting the shipment, expressed in the currency specified in freight_currency. This amount is included in the customs value calculation under the CIF (Cost, Insurance, Freight) valuation method. Must be a non-negative numeric value with up to 2 decimal places. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 12500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The total insurance premium paid to cover the shipment against loss or damage during transit, expressed in the same currency as the freight amount. Under the CIF customs valuation method, this amount is added to the transaction value to determine the customs value. Must be a non-negative numeric value. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 875.00 |
| created_by | Created By | The unique identifier or username of the system user or application account that initially created the shipment record. Used for audit trail, accountability tracking, and data lineage purposes. | VARCHAR(100) | user.ahmed, system_api |
| created_at | Created At | The system-generated timestamp recording the exact date and time when the shipment record was first created in the system. This field is immutable after creation and serves as the audit creation marker. Stored in UTC following ISO 8601 format. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-10T08:45:00Z |
| updated_at | Last Updated At | The system-generated timestamp recording the most recent date and time when the shipment record was modified. This field is automatically updated by the system on every record change and is used for change tracking, synchronization, and audit trail purposes. Must always be greater than or equal to created_at. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15T14:22:30Z |', '2026-03-04 14:16:24.92928');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (142, 49, 'user', 'give me data classification ', '2026-03-04 14:26:23.929077');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (143, 49, 'assistant', 'Here are the data classification levels for the fields in the **shipment** table, based on the Saudi SDAIA NDMO data classification framework:

| Field Name | Classification Level | Classification Rationale | Data Owner | Sensitivity Category |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Restricted | Internal system identifier used for record linkage; exposure could enable unauthorized access to shipment records across systems. | Customs & Trade Operations | Internal Reference |
| shipment_ref_no | Restricted | Business reference number shared with trading partners; limited external exposure but could be used to query shipment status. | Customs & Trade Operations | Internal Reference |
| shipment_type | Public | General classification (Import/Export/Transit) that carries no personal or sensitive business information on its own. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_date | Restricted | Transaction date that forms part of the commercial and customs record; could reveal trade activity patterns if aggregated. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_status | Restricted | Lifecycle status of the shipment; internal operational data whose disclosure could reveal customs clearance progress to unauthorized parties. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| origin_country_code | Public | ISO standard country code representing the shipment origin; widely available and referenced in public trade documents. | Customs & Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| destination_country_code | Public | ISO standard country code representing the shipment destination; widely available and referenced in public trade documents. | Customs & Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| port_of_loading | Public | Name of the port where goods were loaded; appears on publicly available shipping documents such as the Bill of Lading. | Customs & Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| port_of_discharge | Public | Name of the port where goods are unloaded; appears on publicly available shipping documents and trade declarations. | Customs & Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| final_destination | Confidential | Specific delivery address or location of the consignee; reveals physical location details of business premises or individuals, qualifying as PII/sensitive business data. | Customs & Trade Operations | Location / PII |
| incoterm_code | Restricted | Commercial trade term reflecting contractual obligations between buyer and seller; internal to the commercial transaction and not for public disclosure. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| transport_mode | Public | General mode of transport (Sea/Air/Land); non-sensitive operational metadata with no harm potential if disclosed. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| carrier_name | Restricted | Name of the logistics or shipping company; commercially sensitive as it reveals supplier/partner relationships and procurement choices. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| vessel_flight_no | Restricted | Voyage or flight identifier linked to cargo movement; when combined with other fields could reveal cargo manifests and trade intelligence. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| bill_of_lading_no | Confidential | Legal document identifier that grants title to goods; unauthorized access could enable cargo fraud, theft, or diversion of shipments. | Customs & Trade Operations | Legal / Commercial |
| awb_no | Confidential | Air Waybill number serving as a legal transport contract; unauthorized disclosure could enable cargo fraud or unauthorized cargo release. | Customs & Trade Operations | Legal / Commercial |
| container_no | Restricted | Standardized container identifier; when combined with seal and route data could expose shipment details to unauthorized parties. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| container_type | Public | ISO standard container type code (e.g., 20GP, 40HC); generic technical specification with no sensitive content on its own. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| seal_no | Confidential | Security seal number affixed to the container; disclosure could enable tampering, seal forgery, or circumvention of customs security controls. | Customs & Trade Operations | Security / Compliance |
| gross_weight_kg | Restricted | Total shipment weight declared for customs; commercially sensitive when combined with other trade data and used in duty calculation. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| net_weight_kg | Restricted | Net goods weight used for customs duty calculation; commercially sensitive and part of the official customs declaration record. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| volume_cbm | Restricted | Shipment volume used for freight pricing and container planning; commercially sensitive as it reveals cargo size and cost structure. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| total_packages | Restricted | Number of packages in the shipment; part of the customs declaration and packing list; limited sensitivity but internal to the transaction. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| package_type | Public | General packaging type (e.g., CARTON, PALLET); generic operational descriptor with no sensitive content on its own. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| freight_currency | Restricted | Currency of freight payment; reveals aspects of the commercial transaction and international banking relationships. | Finance & Trade Compliance | Financial Data |
| freight_amount | Confidential | Exact freight charges paid to the carrier; commercially sensitive financial data that reveals cost structures, carrier pricing agreements, and forms part of the customs valuation (CIF value). | Finance & Trade Compliance | Financial Data |
| insurance_amount | Confidential | Insurance premium amount for the shipment; commercially sensitive financial data included in the customs valuation calculation and subject to regulatory scrutiny. | Finance & Trade Compliance | Financial Data |
| created_by | Confidential | Username or user ID of the employee who created the record; constitutes personal data (PII) of a ZATCA staff member and is subject to Saudi PDPL. | Data Governance / IT | PII — Employee Data |
| created_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp for record creation; part of the audit trail and should be protected from unauthorized modification or deletion. | Data Governance / IT | Audit / Metadata |
| updated_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp for the last record update; part of the audit trail integrity chain and should be protected from unauthorized alteration. | Data Governance / IT | Audit / Metadata |', '2026-03-04 14:26:53.02559');
