INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (163, 53, 'user', 'ok add business defintions please ', '2026-03-05 12:10:24.694433');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (164, 53, 'assistant', 'Here are the business definitions for all 30 fields in the **shipment** dataset:

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A unique, system-generated identifier assigned to each shipment record at the time of creation. It serves as the primary key of the shipment entity and is used to reference the shipment across all downstream systems, including customs declarations, invoicing, and tracking. This value is immutable and must never be changed after creation. | VARCHAR(50) | SHP-20240315-00042 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A human-readable business reference number assigned by the shipper, freight forwarder, or logistics operator to identify the shipment in external communications, shipping documents, and customer correspondence. Unlike the system-generated shipment_id, this number is meaningful to business stakeholders and appears on Bills of Lading, Air Waybills, and customs declarations. Must be unique per shipment. | VARCHAR(50) | REF-SA-2024-88312 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Classifies the trade direction and customs regime of the shipment. Determines which ZATCA and Saudi Customs regulatory rules apply, including applicable duties, VAT treatment (e.g., zero-rating for exports), and required documentation. Valid values are: IMPORT, EXPORT, RE-EXPORT, TRANSIT, TEMPORARY_IMPORT, TEMPORARY_EXPORT. | VARCHAR(20) | EXPORT |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment was dispatched, handed over to the carrier, or submitted to Saudi Customs. This date serves as the tax point date for ZATCA VAT purposes, the baseline for SLA tracking, and the declaration date on customs documents. Must be in ISO 8601 format (YYYY-MM-DD). | DATE | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Represents the current lifecycle stage of the shipment within the import/export workflow. Drives business process routing, SLA measurement, and regulatory reporting. Status must follow the approved forward-only state machine: DRAFT → CONFIRMED → BOOKED → IN_TRANSIT → ARRIVED → UNDER_CUSTOMS_CLEARANCE → CLEARED → DELIVERED → COMPLETED. CANCELLED and ON_HOLD are permitted from any active state. | VARCHAR(30) | IN_TRANSIT |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 two-letter country code identifying the country from which the shipment originates. Used by Saudi Customs for tariff classification, preferential trade agreement eligibility (e.g., GCC, Arab League), rules of origin verification, and anti-dumping duty assessment. Must reference a valid ISO 3166-1 country. | CHAR(2) | CN |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 Alpha-2 two-letter country code identifying the country to which the shipment is ultimately destined. Determines export licensing requirements, ZATCA VAT zero-rating eligibility for exports, and re-export bond applicability. Must reference a valid ISO 3166-1 country. | CHAR(2) | SA |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The UN/LOCODE identifier of the port, airport, or terminal where the goods are loaded onto the primary mode of transport. Mandatory for sea and air shipments. Appears on the Bill of Lading and Air Waybill. The country prefix of the LOCODE must align with the origin country for direct (non-transit) shipments. | VARCHAR(10) | CNSHA |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The UN/LOCODE identifier of the port, airport, or terminal where goods are unloaded from the primary carrier. For Saudi imports, this is typically Jeddah Islamic Port (SAJED), King Abdulaziz Port Dammam (SADMM), or King Khalid International Airport (SARUH). Mandatory for sea and air shipments and must align with the destination country for direct imports. | VARCHAR(10) | SAJED |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate delivery location of the goods beyond the port of discharge. May be expressed as a city name, address, or facility description. Mandatory for TRANSIT and RE-EXPORT shipments as Saudi Customs requires the ultimate destination for transit bond calculation and route authorization. May contain individual delivery addresses, making it conditionally subject to Saudi PDPL. | VARCHAR(255) | Riyadh, Kingdom of Saudi Arabia |
| incoterm_code | Incoterm Code | The International Commercial Terms (Incoterms 2020) code published by the International Chamber of Commerce (ICC), defining the contractual boundary of responsibility for freight cost, insurance, and risk between the buyer and seller. Directly affects ZATCA customs value calculation (CIF vs. FOB basis) and freight invoice VAT applicability. Must be one of the 11 valid Incoterms 2020 codes. | CHAR(3) | CIF |
| transport_mode | Transport Mode | The primary mode of transport used to move the shipment from origin to destination. Determines which carrier documents are required (Bill of Lading for SEA, Air Waybill for AIR, CMR for ROAD), which Incoterms are applicable, and the Saudi Customs declaration type to be used. Valid values: SEA, AIR, ROAD, RAIL, MULTIMODAL, COURIER. | VARCHAR(15) | SEA |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The full legal name of the shipping carrier, airline, freight operator, or logistics company responsible for physically transporting the shipment. Used for Saudi Customs manifest matching, carrier liability claims, and freight invoice reconciliation. Should reference the organization''s approved carrier registry where possible. | VARCHAR(200) | Maersk Line |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel / Flight Number | The name and voyage number of the vessel (for sea freight) or the IATA flight number (for air freight) carrying the shipment. This identifier appears on the Bill of Lading, Air Waybill, and Saudi Customs manifest. Mandatory for SEA and AIR shipments once the shipment reaches IN_TRANSIT status. | VARCHAR(50) | MSC OSCAR V001E |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique document number of the Bill of Lading (B/L) issued by the ocean carrier to the shipper. The B/L serves as the contract of carriage, receipt of goods, and document of title for sea freight. Mandatory for all SEA transport mode shipments at customs clearance. Must be unique across all sea shipments. Mutually exclusive with awb_no for a given shipment. | VARCHAR(30) | MAEU123456789 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique identifier of the Air Waybill (AWB) issued by the airline or freight forwarder for air cargo shipments. The AWB is the contract of carriage for air freight and is required by Saudi Customs and GAACA for air cargo clearance. Must conform to the IATA format: 3-digit airline prefix + hyphen + 8-digit serial number (e.g., 176-12345678). Mandatory for AIR shipments at customs clearance. Mutually exclusive with bill_of_lading_no. | VARCHAR(15) | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The ISO 6346-compliant unique identification number affixed to the shipping container. Consists of a 4-character owner code, 6-digit serial number, and 1 check digit (e.g., MSCU1234567). Used by Saudi Customs, port authorities, and shipping lines for container tracking, manifest matching, and customs examination. Mandatory for full container load (FCL) sea freight shipments. | CHAR(11) | MSCU1234567 |
| container_type | Container Type | The standardized classification of the shipping container based on ISO standards and shipping industry conventions. Determines port handling procedures, freight rates, customs inspection methods, and reefer/special cargo requirements. Examples: 20GP (20-foot general purpose), 40HC (40-foot high cube), REEFER_20 (refrigerated), BULK. Applicable to SEA transport mode only. | VARCHAR(20) | 40HC |
| seal_no | Seal Number | The alphanumeric identifier of the security seal applied to the container by the carrier or customs authority. Verified by Saudi Customs officers at the port of discharge to confirm container integrity and detect tampering. A broken or unrecorded seal triggers mandatory physical inspection. Mandatory for FCL container shipments at customs clearance. Treated as security-sensitive data. | VARCHAR(20) | SA1234567 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment in kilograms, inclusive of all goods, packaging materials, pallets, and dunnage, but excluding the container tare weight. Used by Saudi Customs for duty calculation, by carriers for freight billing, and by port authorities for equipment planning. Must be greater than zero. Must be stored to a maximum of 3 decimal places (gram precision). | DECIMAL(15,3) | 21000.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The weight of the goods themselves in kilograms, excluding all packaging materials, pallets, and dunnage. Used by Saudi Customs as the basis for specific duty calculation under the Saudi tariff schedule and for trade statistics reporting. Must be greater than zero and must not exceed gross_weight_kg. Must be stored to a maximum of 3 decimal places. | DECIMAL(15,3) | 18500.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total volume of the shipment expressed in cubic meters (CBM — Cubic Meter). Used by freight forwarders for volumetric weight calculation (to compare against actual weight for billing), by carriers for container space optimization, and by warehouses for storage planning. Must be greater than zero when populated. Stored to 3 decimal places. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 48.500 |
| total_packages | Total Packages | The total count of individual packages, cartons, pallets, drums, or handling units comprising the shipment. Must match the packing list count submitted to Saudi Customs. Used by customs officers for physical cargo examination and count verification. Must be a positive integer of at least 1 for all non-draft shipments. | INTEGER | 120 |
| package_type | Package Type | The standardized classification of the type of packaging used for the shipment, based on UN/ECE Recommendation No. 21 package type codes. Affects customs examination procedures, cargo handling instructions, and container loading plans. Examples: CT (Carton), PL (Pallet), DR (Drum), CR (Crate), BG (Bag). Should reference the organization''s approved package type reference table. | VARCHAR(20) | CT |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code in which the freight charge (freight_amount) is denominated. Saudi Customs requires customs value to be declared in Saudi Riyal (SAR); therefore, non-SAR freight amounts must be converted using the Saudi Arabian Monetary Authority (SAMA) official exchange rate at the time of shipment. Must always be populated when freight_amount is not null. | CHAR(3) | USD |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total freight charge payable to the carrier for transporting the shipment, expressed in the currency defined by freight_currency. Included in the CIF customs value calculation for Saudi Customs import duty assessment. Subject to ZATCA VAT (at applicable rate) for freight services rendered in or into Saudi Arabia. Must be a non-negative value; freight credits are handled via separate credit notes. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 7500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The insurance premium or total insured value of the shipment, expressed in the same currency as freight_currency. Included in the customs value calculation for CIF and CIP Incoterm shipments as required by Saudi Customs valuation rules. Mandatory when incoterm_code is CIF or CIP. Must be a non-negative value when populated. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 1500.00 |
| created_by | Created By | The unique identifier or username of the system user who originally created the shipment record. A mandatory audit field required for ZATCA compliance, internal governance, and Saudi NDMO data accountability standards. Directly identifies a natural person and is therefore classified as PII under Saudi PDPL. Should be stored as a user ID referencing the system''s user management table to minimize PII exposure in operational tables. | VARCHAR(100) | USR-00042 |
| created_at | Created At | The system-generated timestamp recording the exact date and time when the shipment record was first created in the system. Expressed in UTC or Arabia Standard Time (AST, UTC+3). Used for SLA measurement, ZATCA audit trail, regulatory reporting timelines, and change data capture (CDC). Must be set automatically by the database at insert time and must never be null or future-dated. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15T10:30:00+03:00 |
| updated_at | Last Updated At | The system-generated timestamp recording the date and time of the most recent modification to the shipment record. Automatically updated by the database on every UPDATE operation. Used for change data capture (CDC), audit trailing, data synchronization between systems, and detecting stale or out-of-date records. Must always be greater than or equal to created_at. Must never be null after the first update. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15T14:45:00+03:00 |', '2026-03-05 12:11:28.69937');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (165, 53, 'user', 'ok give me data classification as well ', '2026-03-05 12:12:06.184961');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (166, 53, 'assistant', 'Here are the data classification levels for all 30 fields in the **shipment** dataset, assessed according to the Saudi SDAIA NDMO data classification framework:

| Field Name | Classification Level | Classification Rationale | Data Owner | Sensitivity Category |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Restricted | System-generated primary key with no personal data, but links to sensitive commercial trade records. Unauthorized disclosure could enable unauthorized tracking of shipment activity. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| shipment_ref_no | Restricted | Business reference number used in external trade documents. Disclosure to unauthorized parties could expose commercial transaction details and enable shipment tracking by third parties. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| shipment_type | Public | High-level trade direction classification (IMPORT/EXPORT/TRANSIT). No personal or financial data. Disclosure causes no harm and is commonly referenced in public trade statistics. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| shipment_date | Restricted | Transaction date tied to customs declarations and ZATCA tax point. On its own, low sensitivity, but in combination with other fields it can reveal commercial trading patterns. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| shipment_status | Restricted | Reflects the live operational lifecycle stage of a shipment. Disclosure could reveal operational vulnerabilities or enable unauthorized interference with in-transit cargo. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| origin_country_code | Public | ISO 3166-1 two-letter country code. National-level geographic data with no personal or commercially sensitive content. Widely used in public trade statistics and customs declarations. | Customs & Trade Operations | Geographic |
| destination_country_code | Public | ISO 3166-1 two-letter destination country code. National-level geographic reference with no personal or sensitive content. Appears in publicly reported trade data. | Customs & Trade Operations | Geographic |
| port_of_loading | Public | UN/LOCODE identifier of a public port or airport infrastructure. Publicly available information with no personal or commercially sensitive content. | Customs & Trade Operations | Geographic |
| port_of_discharge | Public | UN/LOCODE identifier of a public port or airport infrastructure. Publicly available information routinely published in shipping manifests and trade reports. | Customs & Trade Operations | Geographic |
| final_destination | Confidential | May contain individual delivery addresses (street, building, P.O. Box) that identify a natural person''s location. Qualifies as PII location data under Saudi PDPL when linked to individuals. Unauthorized disclosure could cause harm to individuals or expose sensitive commercial delivery details. | Customs & Trade Operations | PII / Location Data |
| incoterm_code | Restricted | Reveals the commercial terms agreed between buyer and seller, which are commercially sensitive trade contract details. Disclosure could expose negotiated trade terms to competitors. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| transport_mode | Public | High-level transport classification (SEA/AIR/ROAD). No personal or financial data. Commonly referenced in logistics and trade statistics without sensitivity. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| carrier_name | Restricted | Identifies the commercial carrier engaged for the shipment. Reveals supplier/vendor relationships and commercial partnerships. Disclosure to unauthorized parties could expose procurement strategies. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| vessel_flight_no | Public | Vessel or flight identifier that is publicly tracked by port authorities, airlines, and shipping line tracking platforms. No personal data. Publicly available operational information. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| bill_of_lading_no | Confidential | Legal document of title for sea freight. Unauthorized disclosure could enable fraudulent cargo release or document forgery, causing serious financial and legal harm. Commercially sensitive and legally significant. | Customs & Trade Operations | Legal / Commercial |
| awb_no | Confidential | Air Waybill number is the legal transport contract for air cargo. Unauthorized disclosure could enable fraudulent cargo tracking, theft, or document misuse. Commercially and legally sensitive. | Customs & Trade Operations | Legal / Commercial |
| container_no | Restricted | ISO 6346 container identifier used for cargo tracking. Publicly trackable via shipping line portals, but in context of this dataset it links to specific shipment records and commercial transactions. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| container_type | Public | Standardized container classification code. No personal or financial data. Publicly referenced in shipping and trade documentation without sensitivity. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| seal_no | Confidential | Security seal number used to verify container integrity at Saudi Customs. Unauthorized disclosure could enable seal number spoofing, customs fraud, or cargo tampering — causing serious harm to customs security. | Customs & Trade Operations | Security / Customs |
| gross_weight_kg | Restricted | Commercial weight measurement used for freight billing and customs duty calculation. In combination with other fields, reveals trade volume and commercial terms. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| net_weight_kg | Restricted | Net cargo weight used for customs duty calculation under the Saudi tariff schedule. Reveals trade volume details and can indicate goods category. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| volume_cbm | Restricted | Volumetric measurement used for freight billing and container planning. Commercially sensitive when combined with weight and freight amount fields to reveal trade economics. Internal use only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| total_packages | Restricted | Package count used in customs manifests. Reveals shipment volume and scale of commercial activity. Internal use only; disclosure could expose business trading volumes. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Operations |
| package_type | Public | Standardized UN/ECE packaging classification code. No personal or financial data. Publicly referenced in shipping documentation without sensitivity. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational |
| freight_currency | Restricted | Currency of the freight transaction. When combined with freight_amount, reveals the financial terms and currency exposure of commercial trade agreements. Internal use only. | Finance & Compliance | Financial |
| freight_amount | Confidential | Actual freight cost in the agreed currency. Reveals commercially negotiated freight rates and financial terms between shipper and carrier. Unauthorized disclosure could cause competitive harm and expose financial transaction details. May be subject to Saudi PDPL when linked to individual traders. | Finance & Compliance | Financial / Commercial |
| insurance_amount | Confidential | Insurance premium or insured value amount. Reveals the declared commercial value of goods and financial risk exposure. Unauthorized disclosure could cause financial harm and expose sensitive valuation details used in ZATCA customs assessments. May be subject to Saudi PDPL when linked to individuals. | Finance & Compliance | Financial / Commercial |
| created_by | Confidential | Directly identifies the natural person (system user) who created the shipment record. Constitutes PII under Saudi PDPL Article 1. Unauthorized disclosure could expose individual employee activity, violate privacy rights, and breach Saudi PDPL obligations — causing harm to the individual and regulatory penalties for the organization. | Data Governance & IT | PII / Employee Data |
| created_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp. No direct personal data on its own, but when combined with created_by forms a personally linked audit record. Internal use only; required for ZATCA audit trail and data governance accountability. | Data Governance & IT | Audit / Operational |
| updated_at | Restricted | System audit timestamp for last record modification. Supports change data capture and audit trailing. No personal data on its own but forms part of the audit record when combined with user-linked fields. Internal use only. | Data Governance & IT | Audit / Operational |', '2026-03-05 12:12:43.251273');
