## 6. 🚨 Top 10 Highest Risk Findings

| # | Finding | Affected Fields | Severity | Potential Business Impact |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **All 30 fields have NULL/empty values in sample data** | All fields | 🔴 Critical | Complete dataset is unusable for ZATCA customs submissions, regulatory reporting, and analytics |
| 2 | **Zero format validation on country codes** | origin_country_code, destination_country_code | 🔴 Critical | Invalid ISO codes will cause ZATCA customs declaration rejection and incorrect duty calculations |
| 3 | **No transport-mode-conditional document enforcement** | bill_of_lading_no, awb_no | 🔴 Critical | Sea shipments without B/L or air shipments without AWB cannot be cleared through Saudi Customs |
| 4 | **No enumeration validation on shipment_type** | shipment_type | 🔴 Critical | Incorrect shipment type classification leads to wrong VAT treatment — zero-rating errors on exports |
| 5 | **No enumeration validation on incoterm_code** | incoterm_code | 🔴 Critical | Invalid Incoterms cause incorrect customs value (CIF/FOB) calculation, resulting in duty underpayment or overpayment |
| 6 | **Gross/Net weight relationship not enforced** | gross_weight_kg, net_weight_kg | 🔴 Critical | Net weight exceeding gross weight is physically impossible and indicates corrupt data in customs declarations |
| 7 | **AWB format not validated against IATA standard** | awb_no | 🟠 High | Non-IATA format AWB numbers are rejected by airline systems and GAACA cargo clearance |
| 8 | **Container number not validated against ISO 6346** | container_no | 🟠 High | Invalid container numbers cause manifest mismatches at Saudi ports, triggering holds and demurrage charges |
