## 12. 💡 Key Recommendations Summary

> **1.** 🔴 **Immediately investigate the null data issue** — confirm whether the file is a template or if there is an ETL/extraction failure before any other action.

> **2.** 🔴 **Never allow a shipment to exit DRAFT status without the 14 mandatory fields populated** — implement a status transition gate in the application layer.

> **3.** 🔴 **Add the missing hs_code and customs_declaration_no fields** — without these, the dataset cannot support full ZATCA customs reporting.

> **4.** 🟠 **Add the exchange_rate_to_sar field and integrate a SAMA daily rate feed** — all non-SAR financial amounts are unusable for customs valuation without this.

> **5.** 🟠 **Implement a shipment_status_history audit table** — the current schema has no way to track when status changed, by whom, or for how long — critical for SLA and ZATCA audit trails.

> **6.** 🟡 **Mask created_by in all non-production environments immediately** — this is a confirmed PII field under Saudi PDPL and must not appear in test or development systems.

> **7.** 🟢 **Build the analytical data model proposed** — the 12-dimension star schema will enable full trade analytics, regulatory reporting, and ZATCA compliance dashboards once real data is available.', '2026-03-05 12:19:44.686155');
