INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (178, 57, 'assistant', 'Here are the business definitions for all fields in the **shipment** sheet:

| Field Name | Business Term | Business Definition | Data Type | Example |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Shipment Identifier | A unique system-generated identifier assigned to each shipment record. Serves as the primary key for the shipment entity and is used to reference the shipment across all related systems and transactions. | INTEGER / BIGINT | 100001 |
| shipment_ref_no | Shipment Reference Number | A human-readable business reference number assigned to the shipment, used for tracking and communication purposes between the shipper, consignee, freight forwarder, and customs authority. May follow an internal naming convention (e.g., SHP-2024-00123). | VARCHAR(50) | SHP-2024-00123 |
| shipment_type | Shipment Type | Indicates whether the shipment is an import or export, and may further classify the nature of the movement (e.g., commercial, personal, re-export, transit). Valid values typically include: IMPORT, EXPORT, RE-EXPORT, TRANSIT. | VARCHAR(20) | EXPORT |
| shipment_date | Shipment Date | The official date on which the shipment was dispatched or handed over to the carrier. This date is used for regulatory reporting, customs declarations, and duty calculation under ZATCA guidelines. Format: YYYY-MM-DD. | DATE | 2024-03-15 |
| shipment_status | Shipment Status | Represents the current lifecycle stage of the shipment within the logistics and customs process. Typical values include: DRAFT, SUBMITTED, IN-TRANSIT, ARRIVED, CLEARED, DELIVERED, CANCELLED. | VARCHAR(30) | IN-TRANSIT |
| origin_country_code | Origin Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the country from which the shipment originated. Used in customs declarations and preferential trade agreement assessments. | VARCHAR(3) | SA |
| destination_country_code | Destination Country Code | The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 or alpha-3 country code representing the country to which the shipment is being sent. Used for export control, duty determination, and trade statistics. | VARCHAR(3) | AE |
| port_of_loading | Port of Loading | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port or airport where the shipment was physically loaded onto the primary carrier. Relevant for sea and air freight shipments and required on the Bill of Lading or Air Waybill. | VARCHAR(100) | JEDDAH ISLAMIC PORT |
| port_of_discharge | Port of Discharge | The name or UN/LOCODE of the port or airport where the shipment is unloaded from the primary carrier. Used in customs clearance documentation and freight cost calculation. | VARCHAR(100) | PORT OF DUBAI (JEBEL ALI) |
| final_destination | Final Destination | The ultimate geographic location (city, address, or facility) where the goods are to be delivered after discharge. May differ from the port of discharge when inland transport is involved. | VARCHAR(200) | Dubai Logistics City, UAE |
| incoterm_code | Incoterms Code | The internationally recognized trade term (Incoterms® 2020, published by the International Chamber of Commerce) that defines the responsibilities of buyers and sellers for delivery, risk transfer, and cost allocation. Valid values: EXW, FCA, CPT, CIP, DAP, DPU, DDP, FAS, FOB, CFR, CIF. | VARCHAR(3) | CIF |
| transport_mode | Mode of Transport | Specifies the primary method of transportation used to move the shipment. Valid values include: SEA, AIR, ROAD, RAIL, MULTIMODAL. Required for customs declarations and freight documentation. | VARCHAR(20) | SEA |
| carrier_name | Carrier Name | The legal name of the shipping company, airline, or logistics provider responsible for transporting the shipment. Used for carrier performance tracking and regulatory reporting. | VARCHAR(150) | Saudi Shipping Company |
| vessel_flight_no | Vessel / Flight Number | The identifier of the vessel (ship name or IMO number) for sea freight, or the flight number for air freight, on which the shipment is transported. Used for tracking and customs pre-arrival processing. | VARCHAR(50) | MSC ANNA / SV723 |
| bill_of_lading_no | Bill of Lading Number | The unique reference number of the Bill of Lading (B/L), a legal document issued by the carrier that serves as a receipt for goods, a contract of carriage, and a document of title. Applicable to sea freight shipments. | VARCHAR(50) | MEDUB1234567 |
| awb_no | Air Waybill Number | The unique reference number of the Air Waybill (AWB), a non-negotiable transport document issued by the air carrier. Applicable to air freight shipments. The standard format follows IATA conventions (e.g., 3-digit airline code + 8-digit serial number). | VARCHAR(20) | 176-12345678 |
| container_no | Container Number | The internationally standardized unique identifier assigned to a shipping container, following the ISO 6346 format (4 letters + 7 digits, e.g., MSCU1234567). Used for container tracking and customs inspection scheduling. | VARCHAR(15) | MSCU1234567 |
| container_type | Container Type | Specifies the type and size of the shipping container used. Common values include: 20GP (20-foot General Purpose), 40GP (40-foot General Purpose), 40HC (40-foot High Cube), 20RF (20-foot Refrigerated), 40OT (40-foot Open Top). | VARCHAR(10) | 40HC |
| seal_no | Seal Number | The unique identifier of the security seal applied to the container or cargo unit after loading. Used by customs authorities to verify that the container has not been tampered with during transit. | VARCHAR(50) | SL-98765432 |
| gross_weight_kg | Gross Weight (KG) | The total weight of the shipment including all goods, packaging materials, and pallets, measured in kilograms. Used for freight cost calculation, weight-based duty assessment, and transport documentation. Must be a positive numeric value. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 5420.500 |
| net_weight_kg | Net Weight (KG) | The weight of the goods only, excluding all packaging materials and pallets, measured in kilograms. Used for customs duty calculation, trade statistics, and product compliance. Must be less than or equal to gross_weight_kg. | DECIMAL(12,3) | 4980.000 |
| volume_cbm | Volume (CBM) | The total cubic measurement of the shipment in cubic meters (CBM — Cubic Meters). Used for volumetric freight pricing, cargo planning, and container utilization calculations. Must be a positive numeric value. | DECIMAL(10,3) | 28.500 |
| total_packages | Total Number of Packages | The total count of individual package units (boxes, pallets, crates, bags, etc.) included in the shipment. Used in cargo manifests, packing lists, and customs declarations. Must be a positive integer. | INTEGER | 120 |
| package_type | Package Type | Describes the type of packaging used for the shipment goods. Common values include: CARTON, PALLET, CRATE, BAG, DRUM, BUNDLE, ROLL. Used for handling instructions and customs documentation. | VARCHAR(30) | PALLET |
| freight_currency | Freight Currency | The ISO 4217 three-letter currency code in which the freight charges are denominated (e.g., SAR, USD, EUR). Used for financial reporting and foreign currency conversion. | VARCHAR(3) | USD |
| freight_amount | Freight Amount | The total cost of transporting the shipment, expressed in the currency specified in freight_currency. Includes base freight charges and may include surcharges. Used for landed cost calculation and financial reporting. Must be a non-negative numeric value. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 3500.00 |
| insurance_amount | Insurance Amount | The monetary value of the insurance coverage obtained for the shipment, expressed in the same or a different currency than freight. Used for risk management, landed cost calculation, and claims processing. Must be a non-negative numeric value. | DECIMAL(18,2) | 450.00 |
| created_by | Created By | The username, employee ID, or system account identifier of the user or process that created the shipment record. Used for audit trail, accountability, and data lineage tracking. | VARCHAR(100) | ahmed.ali |
| created_at | Created At | The system-generated timestamp recording the exact date and time when the shipment record was first created in the system. Used for audit logging and SLA tracking. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS (UTC or local timezone). | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-10 08:45:22 |
| updated_at | Last Updated At | The system-generated timestamp recording the most recent date and time when the shipment record was modified. Automatically updated on every record change. Used for change tracking, data synchronization, and audit purposes. Format: YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS. | TIMESTAMP | 2024-03-15 14:30:05 |', '2026-03-06 02:29:52.33737');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (179, 57, 'user', 'give me data classification ', '2026-03-06 02:30:38.741964');
INSERT INTO messages (id, conversation_id, role, content, created_at) VALUES (180, 57, 'assistant', 'Here are the data classification results for all fields in the **shipment** sheet according to the Saudi SDAIA NDMO classification framework:

| Field Name | Classification Level | Classification Rationale | Data Owner | Sensitivity Category |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| shipment_id | Restricted | Internal system identifier used for record linkage. Disclosure outside the organization could expose system structure and enable unauthorized tracking. | Customs & Trade Operations | Internal Reference |
| shipment_ref_no | Restricted | Business reference number used for internal and partner communication. Limited to authorized trading parties and customs officials. | Customs & Trade Operations | Internal Reference |
| shipment_type | Public | General classification of shipment movement (import/export/transit). No personal or sensitive information; commonly referenced in trade statistics. | Customs & Trade Operations | Trade Classification |
| shipment_date | Restricted | Transaction date tied to a specific shipment record. When combined with other fields, could reveal trade patterns and business activities. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| shipment_status | Restricted | Reflects the current processing stage of a shipment within ZATCA''s customs workflow. Disclosure could compromise enforcement operations or pre-clearance activities. | Customs & Trade Operations | Operational Data |
| origin_country_code | Public | ISO country code indicating shipment origin. Widely used in trade statistics and public customs declarations. No personal or sensitive content on its own. | Customs & Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| destination_country_code | Public | ISO country code indicating shipment destination. Widely available in trade manifests and public statistical reporting. | Customs & Trade Operations | Trade Data |
| port_of_loading | Public | Name of the port where goods were loaded. Publicly referenced in shipping documents, manifests, and trade databases. | Customs & Trade Operations | Logistics Data |
| port_of_discharge | Public | Name of the port where goods are discharged. Publicly referenced in shipping documents and trade statistics. | Customs & Trade Operations | Logistics Data |
| final_destination | Confidential | May contain specific facility addresses, warehouse locations, or consignee delivery points. Disclosure could reveal business locations and supply chain details of private entities. | Customs & Trade Operations | Location / Commercial Data |
| incoterm_code | Restricted | Defines the contractual trade terms between buyer and seller. Reveals commercial arrangements and risk allocation, intended for authorized trading parties only. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| transport_mode | Public | General classification of the transport method used. Publicly referenced in customs declarations and trade statistics. | Customs & Trade Operations | Logistics Data |
| carrier_name | Restricted | Name of the logistics or shipping company. Reveals commercial relationships and carrier selection strategies; restricted to authorized parties. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| vessel_flight_no | Restricted | Vessel or flight identifier linked to a specific shipment. Could be used to track cargo movements and reveal operational patterns. | Customs & Trade Operations | Logistics Data |
| bill_of_lading_no | Confidential | A legally binding document reference number. Provides access to title-of-goods information and is restricted to the shipper, consignee, and authorized customs officials. | Customs & Trade Operations | Legal / Commercial Data |
| awb_no | Confidential | Air Waybill number is a legally significant document identifier linked to air freight contracts and cargo. Access restricted to authorized parties per IATA and customs regulations. | Customs & Trade Operations | Legal / Commercial Data |
| container_no | Restricted | Unique container identifier used for tracking and customs inspection scheduling. Disclosure could enable unauthorized access monitoring or cargo targeting. | Customs & Trade Operations | Logistics Data |
| container_type | Public | Standardized container size and type classification. Publicly referenced in shipping manifests and trade documentation. | Customs & Trade Operations | Logistics Data |
| seal_no | Confidential | Security seal identifier applied to a container after loading. Disclosure could enable tampering, seal duplication, or circumvention of customs inspection controls. | Customs & Trade Operations | Security / Customs Control |
| gross_weight_kg | Restricted | Total shipment weight used for duty calculation and freight pricing. Reveals commercial and operational details; restricted to authorized trade and customs parties. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial / Customs Data |
| net_weight_kg | Restricted | Net goods weight used for duty and tax assessment by ZATCA. Directly tied to customs duty calculations and subject to regulatory confidentiality. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial / Customs Data |
| volume_cbm | Restricted | Volumetric measurement used for freight cost calculation. Reveals cargo details and commercial pricing arrangements restricted to authorized parties. | Customs & Trade Operations | Commercial Data |
| total_packages | Restricted | Count of packages in a shipment. When combined with other fields, reveals cargo details used in customs declarations and duty assessments. | Customs & Trade Operations | Customs / Logistics Data |
| package_type | Public | General packaging classification (e.g., carton, pallet). Commonly referenced in packing lists and public shipping documentation. | Customs & Trade Operations | Logistics Data |
| freight_currency | Restricted | Currency denomination of freight charges. Reveals financial arrangements and may indicate the commercial relationships between trading parties. | Finance & Revenue | Financial Data |
| freight_amount | Confidential | Monetary value of freight charges. Contains commercially sensitive financial information about logistics costs and pricing agreements between trading parties. | Finance & Revenue | Financial / Commercial Data |
| insurance_amount | Confidential | Monetary value of shipment insurance coverage. Contains sensitive financial data used in risk assessment and claims processing; restricted to authorized financial and customs parties. | Finance & Revenue | Financial / Commercial Data |
| created_by | Confidential | Username or employee ID of the record creator. Constitutes personal data under Saudi PDPL as it identifies an individual employee. Subject to privacy protection requirements. | IT / Data Governance | PII / HR Data |
| created_at | Restricted | System timestamp of record creation. Used for audit trails and data lineage; restricted to authorized system administrators and compliance officers. | IT / Data Governance | Audit / Metadata |
| updated_at | Restricted | System timestamp of the last record modification. Used for change tracking and audit purposes; restricted to authorized system administrators and compliance officers. | IT / Data Governance | Audit / Metadata |', '2026-03-06 02:31:07.010951');
